11366 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11367 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11368 bool array::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype) const noexcept
11369 {
11370 if (elems_.empty())
11371 return false;
11372
11373 if (ntype == node_type::none)
11374 ntype = elems_[0]->type();
11375
11376 for (const auto& val : elems_)
11377 if (val->type() != ntype)
11378 return false;
11379
11380 return true;
11381 }
11382
11383 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11384 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11385 bool array::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype, node * &first_nonmatch) noexcept
11386 {
11387 if (elems_.empty())
11388 {
11389 first_nonmatch = {};
11390 return false;
11391 }
11392 if (ntype == node_type::none)
11393 ntype = elems_[0]->type();
11394 for (const auto& val : elems_)
11395 {
11396 if (val->type() != ntype)
11397 {
11398 first_nonmatch = val.get();
11399 return false;
11400 }
11401 }
11402 return true;
11403 }
11404
11405 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11406 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11407 bool array::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype, const node*& first_nonmatch) const noexcept
11408 {
11409 node* fnm = nullptr;
11410 const auto result = const_cast<array&>(*this).is_homogeneous(ntype, fnm);
11411 first_nonmatch = fnm;
11412 return result;
11413 }

11461
11462 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11463 size_t array::total_leaf_count() const noexcept
11464 {
11465 size_t leaves{};
11466 for (size_t i = 0, e = elems_.size(); i < e; i++)
11467 {
11468 auto arr = elems_[i]->as_array();
11469 leaves += arr ? arr->total_leaf_count() : size_t{ 1 };
11470 }
11471 return leaves;
11472 }
11473
11474 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11475 void array::flatten_child(array && child, size_t & dest_index) noexcept
11476 {
11477 for (size_t i = 0, e = child.size(); i < e; i++)
11478 {
11479 auto type = child.elems_[i]->type();
11480 if (type == node_type::array)
11481 {
11482 array& arr = *reinterpret_cast<array*>(child.elems_[i].get());
11483 if (!arr.empty())
11484 flatten_child(std::move(arr), dest_index);
11485 }
11486 else
11487 elems_[dest_index++] = std::move(child.elems_[i]);
11488 }
11489 }
11490
11491 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11492 array& array::flatten()&
11493 {
11494 if (elems_.empty())
11495 return *this;
11496
11497 bool requires_flattening = false;
11498 size_t size_after_flattening = elems_.size();
11499 for (size_t i = elems_.size(); i-- > 0u;)
11500 {
11501 auto arr = elems_[i]->as_array();
11502 if (!arr)
11503 continue;
11504 size_after_flattening--; // discount the array itself
11505 const auto leaf_count = arr->total_leaf_count();
11506 if (leaf_count > 0u)
11507 {
11508 requires_flattening = true;
11509 size_after_flattening += leaf_count;
11510 }
11511 else
11512 elems_.erase(elems_.cbegin() + static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(i));
11513 }
11514
11515 if (!requires_flattening)
11516 return *this;
11517
11518 elems_.reserve(size_after_flattening);
11519
11520 size_t i = 0;
11521 while (i < elems_.size())
11522 {
11523 auto arr = elems_[i]->as_array();
11524 if (!arr)
11525 {
11526 i++;
11527 continue;
11528 }
11529
11530 impl::node_ptr arr_storage = std::move(elems_[i]);
11531 const auto leaf_count = arr->total_leaf_count();
11532 if (leaf_count > 1u)
11533 preinsertion_resize(i + 1u, leaf_count - 1u);
11534 flatten_child(std::move(*arr), i); // increments i
11535 }
11536
11537 return *this;
11538 }
11539
11540 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11541 array& array::prune(bool recursive)& noexcept
11542 {
11543 if (elems_.empty())
11544 return *this;
11545
11546 for (size_t i = elems_.size(); i-- > 0u;)
11547 {
11548 if (auto arr = elems_[i]->as_array())
11549 {
11550 if (recursive)
11551 arr->prune(true);
11552 if (arr->empty())
11553 elems_.erase(elems_.cbegin() + static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(i));
11554 }
11555 else if (auto tbl = elems_[i]->as_table())
11556 {
11557 if (recursive)
11558 tbl->prune(true);
11559 if (tbl->empty())
11560 elems_.erase(elems_.cbegin() + static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(i));
11561 }
11562 }
11563
11564 return *this;
11565 }
11566
11567 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11568 void array::pop_back() noexcept
11569 {
11570 elems_.pop_back();
11571 }
11572
11573 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11574 void array::clear() noexcept
11575 {
11576 elems_.clear();
11577 }
11578
11579 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11580 bool TOML_CALLCONV array::equal(const array& lhs, const array& rhs) noexcept
11581 {
11582 if (&lhs == &rhs)
11583 return true;
11584 if (lhs.elems_.size() != rhs.elems_.size())
11585 return false;
11586 for (size_t i = 0, e = lhs.elems_.size(); i < e; i++)
11587 {
11588 const auto lhs_type = lhs.elems_[i]->type();
11589 const node& rhs_ = *rhs.elems_[i];
11590 const auto rhs_type = rhs_.type();
11591 if (lhs_type != rhs_type)
11592 return false;
11593
11594 const bool equal = lhs.elems_[i]->visit(
11595 [&](const auto& lhs_) noexcept
11596 { return lhs_ == *reinterpret_cast<std::remove_reference_t<decltype(lhs_)>*>(&rhs_); });
11597 if (!equal)
11598 return false;
11599 }
11600 return true;
11601 }
11602}
11603TOML_NAMESPACE_END;
11604

11606#pragma pop_macro("min")
11607#pragma pop_macro("max")
11608#pragma inline_recursion(off)
11609#endif

11641 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11642 table::table(const impl::table_init_pair* b, const impl::table_init_pair* e)
11643 {
11644#if TOML_LIFETIME_HOOKS
11645 TOML_TABLE_CREATED;
11646#endif
11647
11648 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(b);
11649 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(e);
11650 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(b <= e);
11651
11652 if TOML_UNLIKELY(b == e)
11653 return;
11654
11655 for (; b != e; b++)
11656 {
11657 if (!b->value) // empty node_views
11658 continue;
11659
11660 map_.insert_or_assign(std::move(b->key), std::move(b->value));
11661 }
11662 }

11664 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11665 table::table(const table& other) //
11666 : node(other),
11667 inline_{ other.inline_ }
11668 {
11669 for (auto&& [k, v] : other.map_)
11670 map_.emplace_hint(map_.end(), k, impl::make_node(*v));
11671
11672#if TOML_LIFETIME_HOOKS
11673 TOML_TABLE_CREATED;
11674#endif
11675 }

11679 : node(std::move(other)),
11680 map_{ std::move(other.map_) },
11681 inline_{ other.inline_ }
11682 {
11683#if TOML_LIFETIME_HOOKS
11684 TOML_TABLE_CREATED;
11685#endif
11686 }

11689 table& table::operator=(const table& rhs)
11690 {

11692 {
11693 node::operator=(rhs);
11694 map_.clear();
11695 for (auto&& [k, v] : rhs.map_)
11696 map_.emplace_hint(map_.end(), k, impl::make_node(*v));
11697 inline_ = rhs.inline_;
11698 }
11699 return *this;
11700 }

11704 {

11706 {
11707 node::operator=(std::move(rhs));
11708 map_ = std::move(rhs.map_);
11709 inline_ = rhs.inline_;
11710 }
11711 return *this;
11712 }

11714 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11715 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11716 bool table::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype) const noexcept
11717 {
11718 if (map_.empty())
11719 return false;
11720
11721 if (ntype == node_type::none)
11722 ntype = map_.cbegin()->second->type();
11723
11724 for (auto&& [k, v] : map_)
11725 {
11726 TOML_UNUSED(k);
11727 if (v->type() != ntype)
11728 return false;
11729 }
11730
11731 return true;
11732 }
11733
11734 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11735 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11736 bool table::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype, node * &first_nonmatch) noexcept
11737 {
11738 if (map_.empty())
11739 {
11740 first_nonmatch = {};
11741 return false;
11742 }
11743 if (ntype == node_type::none)
11744 ntype = map_.cbegin()->second->type();
11745 for (const auto& [k, v] : map_)
11746 {
11747 TOML_UNUSED(k);
11748 if (v->type() != ntype)
11749 {
11750 first_nonmatch = v.get();
11751 return false;
11752 }
11753 }
11754 return true;
11755 }
11756
11757 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11758 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11759 bool table::is_homogeneous(node_type ntype, const node*& first_nonmatch) const noexcept
11760 {
11761 node* fnm = nullptr;
11762 const auto result = const_cast<table&>(*this).is_homogeneous(ntype, fnm);
11763 first_nonmatch = fnm;
11764 return result;
11765 }

11773 return nullptr;

11778 {

11780
11781#if TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS
11782
11783 if (!n)
11784 {
11785 auto err = "key '"s;
11786 err.append(key);
11787 err.append("' not found in table"sv);
11788 throw std::out_of_range{ err };
11789 }
11790
11791#else
11792
11793 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(n && "key not found in table!");
11794
11795#endif
11796
11797 return *n;
11798 }

11833 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE

11835 {
11836 if (auto it = map_.find(key); it != map_.end())
11837 {

11839 return size_t{ 1 };
11840 }
11841 return size_t{};
11842 }
11843
11844 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11845 table& table::prune(bool recursive)& noexcept
11846 {
11847 if (map_.empty())
11848 return *this;
11849
11850 for (auto it = map_.begin(); it != map_.end();)
11851 {
11852 if (auto arr = it->second->as_array())
11853 {
11854 if (recursive)
11855 arr->prune(true);
11856
11857 if (arr->empty())
11858 {
11859 it = map_.erase(it);
11860 continue;
11861 }
11862 }
11863 else if (auto tbl = it->second->as_table())
11864 {
11865 if (recursive)
11866 tbl->prune(true);
11867
11868 if (tbl->empty())
11869 {
11870 it = map_.erase(it);
11871 continue;
11872 }
11873 }
11874 it++;
11875 }
11876
11877 return *this;
11878 }
11879
11880 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11881 void table::clear() noexcept
11882 {
11883 map_.clear();
11884 }
11885
11886 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11887 table::map_iterator table::insert_with_hint(const_iterator hint, key && k, impl::node_ptr && v)
11888 {
11889 return map_.emplace_hint(const_map_iterator{ hint }, std::move(k), std::move(v));
11890 }
11891
11892 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11893 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11894 bool TOML_CALLCONV table::equal(const table& lhs, const table& rhs) noexcept
11895 {
11896 if (&lhs == &rhs)
11897 return true;
11898 if (lhs.map_.size() != rhs.map_.size())
11899 return false;
11900
11901 for (auto l = lhs.map_.begin(), r = rhs.map_.begin(), e = lhs.map_.end(); l != e; l++, r++)
11902 {
11903 if (l->first != r->first)
11904 return false;
11905
11906 const auto lhs_type = l->second->type();
11907 const node& rhs_ = *r->second;
11908 const auto rhs_type = rhs_.type();
11909 if (lhs_type != rhs_type)
11910 return false;
11911
11912 const bool equal = l->second->visit(
11913 [&](const auto& lhs_) noexcept
11914 { return lhs_ == *reinterpret_cast<std::remove_reference_t<decltype(lhs_)>*>(&rhs_); });
11915 if (!equal)
11916 return false;
11917 }
11918 return true;
11919 }
11920}

11972TOML_IMPL_NAMESPACE_START
11973{
11974 TOML_PURE_GETTER
11975 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
11976 bool is_ascii(const char* str, size_t len) noexcept
11977 {
11978 const char* const end = str + len;
11979
11980#if TOML_HAS_SSE2 && (128 % CHAR_BIT) == 0
11981 {
11982 constexpr size_t chars_per_vector = 128u / CHAR_BIT;
11983
11984 if (const size_t simdable = len - (len % chars_per_vector))
11985 {
11986 __m128i mask = _mm_setzero_si128();
11987 for (const char* const e = str + simdable; str < e; str += chars_per_vector)
11988 {
11989 const __m128i current_bytes = _mm_loadu_si128(reinterpret_cast<const __m128i*>(str));
11990 mask = _mm_or_si128(mask, current_bytes);
11991 }
11992 const __m128i has_error = _mm_cmpgt_epi8(_mm_setzero_si128(), mask);
11993
11994#if TOML_HAS_SSE4_1
11995 if (!_mm_testz_si128(has_error, has_error))
11996 return false;
11997#else
11998 if (_mm_movemask_epi8(_mm_cmpeq_epi8(has_error, _mm_setzero_si128())) != 0xFFFF)
11999 return false;
12000#endif
12001 }
12002 }
12003#endif
12004
12005 for (; str < end; str++)
12006 if (static_cast<unsigned char>(*str) > 127u)
12007 return false;
12008
12009 return true;
12010 }
12011}

12036#endif

12047TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE_START
12048{
12049 template <typename T>
12050 class utf8_byte_stream;
12051
12052 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
12053 constexpr auto utf8_byte_order_mark = "\xEF\xBB\xBF"sv;
12054
12055 template <typename Char>
12056 class utf8_byte_stream<std::basic_string_view<Char>>
12057 {
12058 static_assert(sizeof(Char) == 1);
12059
12060 private:
12061 std::basic_string_view<Char> source_;
12062 size_t position_ = {};
12063
12064 public:
12065 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12066 explicit constexpr utf8_byte_stream(std::basic_string_view<Char> sv) noexcept //
12067 : source_{ sv }
12068 {
12069 // skip bom
12070 if (source_.length() >= 3u && memcmp(utf8_byte_order_mark.data(), source_.data(), 3u) == 0)
12071 position_ += 3u;
12072 }
12073
12074 TOML_CONST_INLINE_GETTER
12075 constexpr bool error() const noexcept
12076 {
12077 return false;
12078 }
12079
12080 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12081 constexpr bool eof() const noexcept
12082 {
12083 return position_ >= source_.length();
12084 }
12085
12086 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12087 explicit constexpr operator bool() const noexcept
12088 {
12089 return !eof();
12090 }
12091
12092 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12093 constexpr bool peek_eof() const noexcept
12094 {
12095 return eof();
12096 }
12097
12098 TOML_NODISCARD
12099 TOML_ATTR(nonnull)
12100 size_t operator()(void* dest, size_t num) noexcept
12101 {
12102 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!eof());
12103
12104 num = impl::min(position_ + num, source_.length()) - position_;
12105 std::memcpy(dest, source_.data() + position_, num);
12106 position_ += num;
12107 return num;
12108 }
12109 };
12110
12111 template <>
12112 class utf8_byte_stream<std::istream>
12113 {
12114 private:
12115 std::istream* source_;
12116
12117 public:
12118 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12119 explicit utf8_byte_stream(std::istream& stream) noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) //
12120 : source_{ &stream }
12121 {
12122 if (!*this) // eof, bad
12123 return;
12124
12125 const auto initial_pos = source_->tellg();
12126 char bom[3];
12127 source_->read(bom, 3);
12128 if (source_->bad() || (source_->gcount() == 3 && memcmp(utf8_byte_order_mark.data(), bom, 3u) == 0))
12129 return;
12130
12131 source_->clear();
12132 source_->seekg(initial_pos, std::istream::beg);
12133 }
12134
12135 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12136 bool error() const noexcept
12137 {
12138 return !!(source_->rdstate() & std::istream::badbit);
12139 }
12140
12141 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12142 bool eof() const noexcept
12143 {
12144 return !!(source_->rdstate() & std::istream::eofbit);
12145 }
12146
12147 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12148 explicit operator bool() const noexcept
12149 {
12150 return !(source_->rdstate() & (std::istream::badbit | std::istream::eofbit));
12151 }
12152
12153 TOML_NODISCARD
12154 bool peek_eof() const noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12155 {
12156 return eof() || source_->peek() == std::istream::traits_type::eof();
12157 }
12158
12159 TOML_NODISCARD
12160 TOML_ATTR(nonnull)
12161 size_t operator()(void* dest, size_t num) noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12162 {
12163 TOML_ASSERT(*this);
12164
12165 source_->read(static_cast<char*>(dest), static_cast<std::streamsize>(num));
12166 return static_cast<size_t>(source_->gcount());
12167 }
12168 };
12169
12170 struct utf8_codepoint
12171 {
12172 char32_t value;
12173 char bytes[4];
12174 size_t count;
12175 source_position position;
12176
12177 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12178 constexpr operator const char32_t&() const noexcept
12179 {
12180 return value;
12181 }
12182
12183 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12184 constexpr const char32_t& operator*() const noexcept
12185 {
12186 return value;
12187 }
12188 };
12189 static_assert(std::is_trivial_v<utf8_codepoint>);
12190 static_assert(std::is_standard_layout_v<utf8_codepoint>);
12191
12192 struct TOML_ABSTRACT_INTERFACE utf8_reader_interface
12193 {
12194 TOML_NODISCARD
12195 virtual const source_path_ptr& source_path() const noexcept = 0;
12196
12197 TOML_NODISCARD
12198 virtual const utf8_codepoint* read_next() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) = 0;
12199
12200 TOML_NODISCARD
12201 virtual bool peek_eof() const noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) = 0;
12202
12203#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12204
12205 TOML_NODISCARD
12206 virtual optional<parse_error>&& error() noexcept = 0;
12207
12208#endif
12209
12210 virtual ~utf8_reader_interface() noexcept = default;
12211 };
12212
12213#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12214#define utf8_reader_error(...) throw parse_error(__VA_ARGS__)
12215#define utf8_reader_return_after_error(...) static_assert(true)
12216#define utf8_reader_error_check(...) static_assert(true)
12217#else
12218#define utf8_reader_error(...) err_.emplace(__VA_ARGS__)
12219#define utf8_reader_return_after_error(...) return __VA_ARGS__
12220#define utf8_reader_error_check(...) \
12221 do \
12222 { \
12223 if TOML_UNLIKELY(err_) \
12224 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12225 } \
12226 while (false)
12227
12228#endif
12229
12230#if defined(__APPLE__) || defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__MINGW64__)
12231#define TOML_OVERALIGNED
12232#else
12233#define TOML_OVERALIGNED alignas(32)
12234#endif
12235
12236 template <typename T>
12237 class TOML_EMPTY_BASES utf8_reader final : public utf8_reader_interface
12238 {
12239 private:
12240 static constexpr size_t block_capacity = 32;
12241 utf8_byte_stream<T> stream_;
12242 source_position next_pos_ = { 1, 1 };
12243
12244 impl::utf8_decoder decoder_;
12245 struct currently_decoding_t
12246 {
12247 char bytes[4];
12248 size_t count;
12249 } currently_decoding_;
12250
12251 struct codepoints_t
12252 {
12253 TOML_OVERALIGNED utf8_codepoint buffer[block_capacity];
12254 size_t current;
12255 size_t count;
12256 } codepoints_;
12257
12258 source_path_ptr source_path_;
12259
12260#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12261 optional<parse_error> err_;
12262#endif
12263
12264 bool read_next_block() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12265 {
12266 TOML_ASSERT(stream_);
12267
12268 TOML_OVERALIGNED char raw_bytes[block_capacity];
12269 size_t raw_bytes_read;
12270
12271 // read the next raw (encoded) block in from the stream
12272 if constexpr (noexcept(stream_(raw_bytes, block_capacity)) || !TOML_EXCEPTIONS)
12273 {
12274 raw_bytes_read = stream_(raw_bytes, block_capacity);
12275 }
12276#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12277 else
12278 {
12279 try
12280 {
12281 raw_bytes_read = stream_(raw_bytes, block_capacity);
12282 }
12283 catch (const std::exception& exc)
12284 {
12285 throw parse_error{ exc.what(), next_pos_, source_path_ };
12286 }
12287 catch (...)
12288 {
12289 throw parse_error{ "An unspecified error occurred", next_pos_, source_path_ };
12290 }
12291 }
12292#endif // TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12293
12294 // handle a zero-byte read
12295 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!raw_bytes_read)
12296 {
12297 if (stream_.eof())
12298 {
12299 // EOF only sets the error state if the decoder wants more input, otherwise
12300 // a zero-byte read might have just caused the underlying stream to realize it's exhaused and set
12301 // the EOF flag, and that's totally fine
12302 if (decoder_.needs_more_input())
12303 utf8_reader_error("Encountered EOF during incomplete utf-8 code point sequence",
12304 next_pos_,
12305 source_path_);
12306 }
12307 else
12308 {
12309 utf8_reader_error("Reading from the underlying stream failed - zero bytes read",
12310 next_pos_,
12311 source_path_);
12312 }
12313 return false;
12314 }
12315
12316 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(raw_bytes_read);
12317 std::memset(&codepoints_, 0, sizeof(codepoints_));
12318
12319 // helper for calculating decoded codepoint line+cols
12320 const auto calc_positions = [&]() noexcept
12321 {
12322 for (size_t i = 0; i < codepoints_.count; i++)
12323 {
12324 auto& cp = codepoints_.buffer[i];
12325 cp.position = next_pos_;
12326
12327 if (cp == U'\n')
12328 {
12329 next_pos_.line++;
12330 next_pos_.column = source_index{ 1 };
12331 }
12332 else
12333 next_pos_.column++;
12334 }
12335 };
12336
12337 // decide whether we need to use the UTF-8 decoder or if we can treat this block as plain ASCII
12338 const auto ascii_fast_path = !decoder_.needs_more_input() && impl::is_ascii(raw_bytes, raw_bytes_read);
12339
12340 // ASCII fast-path
12341 if (ascii_fast_path)
12342 {
12343 decoder_.reset();
12344 currently_decoding_.count = {};
12345
12346 codepoints_.count = raw_bytes_read;
12347 for (size_t i = 0; i < codepoints_.count; i++)
12348 {
12349 auto& cp = codepoints_.buffer[i];
12350 cp.value = static_cast<char32_t>(raw_bytes[i]);
12351 cp.bytes[0] = raw_bytes[i];
12352 cp.count = 1u;
12353 }
12354 }
12355
12356 // UTF-8 slow-path
12357 else
12358 {
12359 // helper for getting precise error location
12360 const auto error_pos = [&]() noexcept -> const source_position&
12361 { //
12362 return codepoints_.count ? codepoints_.buffer[codepoints_.count - 1u].position : next_pos_;
12363 };
12364
12365 for (size_t i = 0; i < raw_bytes_read; i++)
12366 {
12367 decoder_(static_cast<uint8_t>(raw_bytes[i]));
12368 if TOML_UNLIKELY(decoder_.error())
12369 {
12370 calc_positions();
12371 utf8_reader_error("Encountered invalid utf-8 sequence", error_pos(), source_path_);
12372 utf8_reader_return_after_error(false);
12373 }
12374
12375 currently_decoding_.bytes[currently_decoding_.count++] = raw_bytes[i];
12376
12377 if (decoder_.has_code_point())
12378 {
12379 auto& cp = codepoints_.buffer[codepoints_.count++];
12380
12381 cp.value = decoder_.codepoint;
12382 cp.count = currently_decoding_.count;
12383 std::memcpy(cp.bytes, currently_decoding_.bytes, currently_decoding_.count);
12384 currently_decoding_.count = {};
12385 }
12386 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(currently_decoding_.count == 4u)
12387 {
12388 calc_positions();
12389 utf8_reader_error("Encountered overlong utf-8 sequence", error_pos(), source_path_);
12390 utf8_reader_return_after_error(false);
12391 }
12392 }
12393 if TOML_UNLIKELY(decoder_.needs_more_input() && stream_.eof())
12394 {
12395 calc_positions();
12396 utf8_reader_error("Encountered EOF during incomplete utf-8 code point sequence",
12397 error_pos(),
12398 source_path_);
12399 utf8_reader_return_after_error(false);
12400 }
12401 }
12402
12403 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(codepoints_.count);
12404 calc_positions();
12405
12406 // handle general I/O errors
12407 // (down here so the next_pos_ benefits from calc_positions())
12408 if TOML_UNLIKELY(stream_.error())
12409 {
12410 utf8_reader_error("An I/O error occurred while reading from the underlying stream",
12411 next_pos_,
12412 source_path_);
12413 utf8_reader_return_after_error(false);
12414 }
12415
12416 return true;
12417 }
12418
12419 public:
12420 template <typename U, typename String = std::string_view>
12421 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12422 explicit utf8_reader(U&& source, String&& source_path = {}) noexcept(
12423 std::is_nothrow_constructible_v<utf8_byte_stream<T>, U&&>)
12424 : stream_{ static_cast<U&&>(source) }
12425 {
12426 currently_decoding_.count = {};
12427
12428 codepoints_.current = {};
12429 codepoints_.count = {};
12430
12431 if (!source_path.empty())
12432 source_path_ = std::make_shared<const std::string>(static_cast<String&&>(source_path));
12433 }
12434
12435 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12436 const source_path_ptr& source_path() const noexcept final
12437 {
12438 return source_path_;
12439 }
12440
12441 TOML_NODISCARD
12442 const utf8_codepoint* read_next() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) final
12443 {
12444 utf8_reader_error_check({});
12445
12446 if (codepoints_.current == codepoints_.count)
12447 {
12448 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!stream_ || !read_next_block())
12449 return nullptr;
12450
12451 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!codepoints_.current);
12452 }
12453 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(codepoints_.count);
12454 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(codepoints_.count <= block_capacity);
12455 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(codepoints_.current < codepoints_.count);
12456
12457 return &codepoints_.buffer[codepoints_.current++];
12458 }
12459
12460 TOML_NODISCARD
12461 bool peek_eof() const noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS) final
12462 {
12463 return stream_.peek_eof();
12464 }
12465
12466#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12467
12468 TOML_NODISCARD
12469 optional<parse_error>&& error() noexcept final
12470 {
12471 return std::move(err_);
12472 }
12473
12474#endif
12475 };

12478 utf8_reader(std::basic_string_view<Char>, std::string_view) -> utf8_reader<std::basic_string_view<Char>>;
12479 template <typename Char>
12480 utf8_reader(std::basic_string_view<Char>, std::string &&) -> utf8_reader<std::basic_string_view<Char>>;
12481 template <typename Char>
12482 utf8_reader(std::basic_istream<Char>&, std::string_view) -> utf8_reader<std::basic_istream<Char>>;
12483 template <typename Char>

12486#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12487#define utf8_buffered_reader_error_check(...) static_assert(true)
12488#else
12489#define utf8_buffered_reader_error_check(...) \
12490 do \
12491 { \
12492 if TOML_UNLIKELY(reader_.error()) \
12493 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12494 } \
12495 while (false)
12496
12497#endif
12498
12499 class TOML_EMPTY_BASES utf8_buffered_reader
12500 {
12501 public:
12502 static constexpr size_t max_history_length = 128;
12503
12504 private:
12505 static constexpr size_t history_buffer_size = max_history_length - 1; //'head' is stored in the reader
12506 utf8_reader_interface& reader_;
12507 struct
12508 {
12509 utf8_codepoint buffer[history_buffer_size];
12510 size_t count, first;
12511 } history_ = {};
12512 const utf8_codepoint* head_ = {};
12513 size_t negative_offset_ = {};
12514
12515 public:
12516 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12517 explicit utf8_buffered_reader(utf8_reader_interface& reader) noexcept //
12518 : reader_{ reader }
12519 {}
12520
12521 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12522 const source_path_ptr& source_path() const noexcept
12523 {
12524 return reader_.source_path();
12525 }
12526
12527 TOML_NODISCARD
12528 const utf8_codepoint* read_next() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12529 {
12530 utf8_buffered_reader_error_check({});
12531
12532 if (negative_offset_)
12533 {
12534 negative_offset_--;
12535
12536 // an entry negative offset of 1 just means "replay the current head"
12537 if (!negative_offset_)
12538 return head_;
12539
12540 // otherwise step back into the history buffer
12541 else
12542 return history_.buffer
12543 + ((history_.first + history_.count - negative_offset_) % history_buffer_size);
12544 }
12545 else
12546 {
12547 // first character read from stream
12548 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!history_.count && !head_)
12549 head_ = reader_.read_next();
12550
12551 // subsequent characters and not eof
12552 else if (head_)
12553 {
12554 if TOML_UNLIKELY(history_.count < history_buffer_size)
12555 history_.buffer[history_.count++] = *head_;
12556 else
12557 history_.buffer[(history_.first++ + history_buffer_size) % history_buffer_size] = *head_;
12558
12559 head_ = reader_.read_next();
12560 }
12561
12562 return head_;
12563 }
12564 }
12565
12566 TOML_NODISCARD
12567 const utf8_codepoint* step_back(size_t count) noexcept
12568 {
12569 utf8_buffered_reader_error_check({});
12570
12571 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(history_.count);
12572 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(negative_offset_ + count <= history_.count);
12573
12574 negative_offset_ += count;
12575
12576 return negative_offset_
12577 ? history_.buffer + ((history_.first + history_.count - negative_offset_) % history_buffer_size)
12578 : head_;
12579 }
12580
12581 TOML_NODISCARD
12582 bool peek_eof() const noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
12583 {
12584 return reader_.peek_eof();
12585 }
12586
12587#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12588
12589 TOML_NODISCARD
12590 optional<parse_error>&& error() noexcept
12591 {
12592 return reader_.error();
12593 }
12594
12595#endif
12596 };
12597}

12684
12685 TOML_PURE_GETTER
12686 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
12687 std::string_view to_sv(const utf8_codepoint& cp) noexcept
12688 {
12689 if (cp.value <= U'\x1F')
12690 return impl::control_char_escapes[cp.value];
12691 else if (cp.value == U'\x7F')
12692 return "\\u007F"sv;
12693 else
12694 return std::string_view{ cp.bytes, cp.count };
12695 }

12700 {

12702 return to_sv(*cp);
12703 return ""sv;
12704 }

12706 struct escaped_codepoint
12707 {
12708 const utf8_codepoint& cp;
12709 };
12710
12711 template <typename T>
12712 TOML_ATTR(nonnull)
12713 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
12714 void concatenate(char*& write_pos, char* const buf_end, const T& arg) noexcept
12715 {
12716 if TOML_UNLIKELY(write_pos >= buf_end)
12717 return;
12718
12719 using arg_type = impl::remove_cvref<T>;
12720
12721 // string views
12722 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<arg_type, std::string_view>)
12723 {
12724 const auto max_chars = static_cast<size_t>(buf_end - write_pos);
12725 const auto len = max_chars < arg.length() ? max_chars : arg.length();
12726 std::memcpy(write_pos, arg.data(), len);
12727 write_pos += len;
12728 }
12729
12730 // doubles
12731 else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<arg_type, double>)
12732 {
12733#if TOML_FLOAT_CHARCONV
12734 const auto result = std::to_chars(write_pos, buf_end, arg);
12735 write_pos = result.ptr;
12736#else
12737 std::ostringstream ss;
12738 ss.imbue(std::locale::classic());
12739 ss.precision(std::numeric_limits<arg_type>::max_digits10);
12740 ss << arg;
12741 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, to_sv(std::move(ss).str()));
12742#endif
12743 }
12744
12745 // 64-bit integers
12746 else if constexpr (impl::is_one_of<arg_type, int64_t, uint64_t>)
12747 {
12748#if TOML_INT_CHARCONV
12749 const auto result = std::to_chars(write_pos, buf_end, arg);
12750 write_pos = result.ptr;
12751#else
12752 std::ostringstream ss;
12753 ss.imbue(std::locale::classic());
12754 using cast_type = std::conditional_t<std::is_signed_v<arg_type>, int64_t, uint64_t>;
12755 ss << static_cast<cast_type>(arg);
12756 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, to_sv(std::move(ss).str()));
12757#endif
12758 }
12759
12760 // escaped_codepoint
12761 else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<arg_type, escaped_codepoint>)
12762 {
12763 if (arg.cp.value <= U'\x7F')
12764 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, to_sv(arg.cp));
12765 else
12766 {
12767 auto val = static_cast<uint_least32_t>(arg.cp.value);
12768 const auto digits = val > 0xFFFFu ? 8u : 4u;
12769 constexpr auto mask = uint_least32_t{ 0xFu };
12770 char buf[10] = { '\\', digits > 4 ? 'U' : 'u' };
12771 for (auto i = 2u + digits; i-- > 2u;)
12772 {
12773 const auto hexdig = val & mask;
12774 buf[i] = static_cast<char>(hexdig >= 0xAu ? ('A' + (hexdig - 0xAu)) : ('0' + hexdig));
12775 val >>= 4;
12776 }
12777 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, std::string_view{ buf, digits + 2u });
12778 }
12779 }
12780
12781 // all other floats (fallback - coerce to double)
12782 else if constexpr (std::is_floating_point_v<arg_type>)
12783 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, static_cast<double>(arg));
12784
12785 // all other integers (fallback - coerce to (u)int64_t)
12786 else if constexpr (std::is_arithmetic_v<arg_type> && std::is_integral_v<arg_type>)
12787 {
12788 using cast_type = std::conditional_t<std::is_unsigned_v<arg_type>, uint64_t, int64_t>;
12789 concatenate(write_pos, buf_end, static_cast<cast_type>(arg));
12790 }
12791
12792 else
12793 {
12794 static_assert(
12795 impl::dependent_false<T>,
12796 "concatenate() inputs are limited to std::string_views, integers, floats, and escaped_codepoint");
12797 }
12798 }
12799
12800 struct error_builder
12801 {
12802 static constexpr std::size_t buf_size = 512;
12803 char buf[buf_size];
12804 char* write_pos = buf;
12805 char* const max_write_pos = buf + (buf_size - std::size_t{ 1 }); // allow for null terminator
12806
12807 TOML_NODISCARD_CTOR
12808 error_builder(std::string_view scope) noexcept
12809 {
12810 concatenate(write_pos, max_write_pos, "Error while parsing "sv);
12811 concatenate(write_pos, max_write_pos, scope);
12812 concatenate(write_pos, max_write_pos, ": "sv);
12813 }
12814
12815 template <typename T>
12816 void append(const T& arg) noexcept
12817 {
12818 concatenate(write_pos, max_write_pos, arg);
12819 }
12820
12821 TOML_RETURNS_BY_THROWING
12822 auto finish(const source_position& pos, const source_path_ptr& source_path) const
12823 {
12824 *write_pos = '\0';
12825
12826#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12827 throw parse_error{ buf, pos, source_path };
12828#else
12829 return parse_error{ std::string(buf, static_cast<size_t>(write_pos - buf)), pos, source_path };
12830#endif
12831 }
12832
12833 TOML_DELETE_DEFAULTS(error_builder);
12834 };

12860 struct parse_key_buffer
12861 {
12862 std::string buffer;
12863 std::vector<std::pair<size_t, size_t>> segments;
12864 std::vector<source_position> starts;
12865 std::vector<source_position> ends;
12866
12867 void clear() noexcept
12868 {
12869 buffer.clear();
12870 segments.clear();
12871 starts.clear();
12872 ends.clear();
12873 }
12874
12875 void push_back(std::string_view segment, source_position b, source_position e)
12876 {
12877 segments.push_back({ buffer.length(), segment.length() });
12878 buffer.append(segment);
12879 starts.push_back(b);
12880 ends.push_back(e);
12881 }
12882
12883 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12884 std::string_view operator[](size_t i) const noexcept
12885 {
12886 return std::string_view{ buffer.c_str() + segments[i].first, segments[i].second };
12887 }
12888
12889 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12890 std::string_view back() const noexcept
12891 {
12892 return (*this)[segments.size() - 1u];
12893 }
12894
12895 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12896 bool empty() const noexcept
12897 {
12898 return segments.empty();
12899 }
12900
12901 TOML_PURE_INLINE_GETTER
12902 size_t size() const noexcept
12903 {
12904 return segments.size();
12905 }
12906 };

12954#if 1 // parser helper macros
12955
12956// Q: "what the fuck is this? MACROS????"
12957// A: The parser needs to work in exceptionless mode (returning error objects directly)
12958// and exception mode (reporting parse failures by throwing). Two totally different control flows.
12959// These macros encapsulate the differences between the two modes so I can write code code
12960// as though I was only targeting one mode and not want yeet myself into the sun.
12961// They're all #undef'd at the bottom of the parser's implementation so they should be harmless outside
12962// of toml++.
12963
12964#define is_eof() !cp
12965#define assert_not_eof() TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(cp != nullptr)
12966#define return_if_eof(...) \
12967 do \
12968 { \
12969 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_eof()) \
12970 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12971 } \
12972 while (false)
12973
12974#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
12975#define is_error() false
12976#define return_after_error(...) TOML_UNREACHABLE
12977#define assert_not_error() static_assert(true)
12978#define return_if_error(...) static_assert(true)
12979#define return_if_error_or_eof(...) return_if_eof(__VA_ARGS__)
12980#else
12981#define is_error() !!err
12982#define return_after_error(...) return __VA_ARGS__
12983#define assert_not_error() TOML_ASSERT(!is_error())
12984#define return_if_error(...) \
12985 do \
12986 { \
12987 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_error()) \
12988 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12989 } \
12990 while (false)
12991#define return_if_error_or_eof(...) \
12992 do \
12993 { \
12994 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_eof() || is_error()) \
12995 return __VA_ARGS__; \
12996 } \
12997 while (false)
12998#endif
12999
13000#if defined(TOML_BREAK_AT_PARSE_ERRORS) && TOML_BREAK_AT_PARSE_ERRORS
13001#if defined(__has_builtin)
13002#if __has_builtin(__builtin_debugtrap)
13003#define parse_error_break() __builtin_debugtrap()
13004#elif __has_builtin(__debugbreak)
13005#define parse_error_break() __debugbreak()
13006#endif
13007#endif
13008#ifndef parse_error_break
13009#if TOML_MSVC || TOML_ICC
13010#define parse_error_break() __debugbreak()
13011#else
13012#define parse_error_break() TOML_ASSERT(false)
13013#endif
13014#endif
13015#else
13016#define parse_error_break() static_assert(true)
13017#endif
13018
13019#define set_error_and_return(ret, ...) \
13020 do \
13021 { \
13022 if (!is_error()) \
13023 set_error(__VA_ARGS__); \
13024 return_after_error(ret); \
13025 } \
13026 while (false)
13027
13028#define set_error_and_return_default(...) set_error_and_return({}, __VA_ARGS__)
13029
13030#define set_error_and_return_if_eof(...) \
13031 do \
13032 { \
13033 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_eof()) \
13034 set_error_and_return(__VA_ARGS__, "encountered end-of-file"sv); \
13035 } \
13036 while (false)
13037
13038#define advance_and_return_if_error(...) \
13039 do \
13040 { \
13041 assert_not_eof(); \
13042 advance(); \
13043 return_if_error(__VA_ARGS__); \
13044 } \
13045 while (false)
13046
13047#define advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof(...) \
13048 do \
13049 { \
13050 assert_not_eof(); \
13051 advance(); \
13052 return_if_error(__VA_ARGS__); \
13053 set_error_and_return_if_eof(__VA_ARGS__); \
13054 } \
13055 while (false)
13056
13057#endif // parser helper macros
13058
13059TOML_IMPL_NAMESPACE_START
13060{
13061 TOML_ABI_NAMESPACE_BOOL(TOML_EXCEPTIONS, impl_ex, impl_noex);
13062
13063 class parser
13064 {
13065 private:
13066 static constexpr size_t max_nested_values = TOML_MAX_NESTED_VALUES;
13067
13068 utf8_buffered_reader reader;
13069 table root;
13070 source_position prev_pos = { 1, 1 };
13071 const utf8_codepoint* cp = {};
13072 std::vector<table*> implicit_tables;
13073 std::vector<table*> dotted_key_tables;
13074 std::vector<table*> open_inline_tables;
13075 std::vector<array*> table_arrays;
13076 parse_key_buffer key_buffer;
13077 std::string string_buffer;
13078 std::string recording_buffer; // for diagnostics
13079 bool recording = false, recording_whitespace = true;
13080 std::string_view current_scope;
13081 size_t nested_values = {};
13082#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
13083 mutable optional<parse_error> err;
13084#endif
13085
13086 TOML_NODISCARD
13087 source_position current_position(source_index fallback_offset = 0) const noexcept
13088 {
13089 if (!is_eof())
13090 return cp->position;
13091 return { prev_pos.line, static_cast<source_index>(prev_pos.column + fallback_offset) };
13092 }
13093
13094 template <typename... T>
13095 TOML_RETURNS_BY_THROWING
13096 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13097 void set_error_at(source_position pos, const T&... reason) const
13098 {
13099 static_assert(sizeof...(T) > 0);
13100 return_if_error();
13101
13102 error_builder builder{ current_scope };
13103 (builder.append(reason), ...);
13104
13105 parse_error_break();
13106
13107#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
13108 builder.finish(pos, reader.source_path());
13109#else
13110 err.emplace(builder.finish(pos, reader.source_path()));
13111#endif
13112 }
13113
13114 template <typename... T>
13115 TOML_RETURNS_BY_THROWING
13116 void set_error(const T&... reason) const
13117 {
13118 set_error_at(current_position(1), reason...);
13119 }
13120
13121 void go_back(size_t count = 1) noexcept
13122 {
13123 return_if_error();
13124 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(count);
13125
13126 cp = reader.step_back(count);
13127 prev_pos = cp->position;
13128 }
13129
13130 void advance()
13131 {
13132 return_if_error();
13133 assert_not_eof();
13134
13135 prev_pos = cp->position;
13136 cp = reader.read_next();
13137
13138#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
13139 if (reader.error())
13140 {
13141 err = std::move(reader.error());
13142 return;
13143 }
13144#endif
13145
13146 if (recording && !is_eof())
13147 {
13148 if (recording_whitespace || !is_whitespace(*cp))
13149 recording_buffer.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13150 }
13151 }
13152
13153 void start_recording(bool include_current = true) noexcept
13154 {
13155 return_if_error();
13156
13157 recording = true;
13158 recording_whitespace = true;
13159 recording_buffer.clear();
13160 if (include_current && !is_eof())
13161 recording_buffer.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13162 }
13163
13164 void stop_recording(size_t pop_bytes = 0) noexcept
13165 {
13166 return_if_error();
13167
13168 recording = false;
13169 if (pop_bytes)
13170 {
13171 if (pop_bytes >= recording_buffer.length())
13172 recording_buffer.clear();
13173 else if (pop_bytes == 1u)
13174 recording_buffer.pop_back();
13175 else
13176 recording_buffer.erase(recording_buffer.begin()
13177 + static_cast<ptrdiff_t>(recording_buffer.length() - pop_bytes),
13178 recording_buffer.end());
13179 }
13180 }
13181
13182 bool consume_leading_whitespace()
13183 {
13184 return_if_error_or_eof({});
13185
13186 bool consumed = false;
13187 while (!is_eof() && is_horizontal_whitespace(*cp))
13188 {
13189 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!is_ascii_horizontal_whitespace(*cp))
13190 set_error_and_return_default("expected space or tab, saw '"sv, escaped_codepoint{ *cp }, "'"sv);
13191
13192 consumed = true;
13193 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13194 }
13195 return consumed;
13196 }
13197
13198 bool consume_line_break()
13199 {
13200 return_if_error_or_eof({});
13201
13202 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_match(*cp, U'\v', U'\f'))
13203 set_error_and_return_default(
13204 R"(vertical tabs '\v' and form-feeds '\f' are not legal line breaks in TOML)"sv);
13205
13206 if (*cp == U'\r')
13207 {
13208 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip \r
13209
13210 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_eof())
13211 set_error_and_return_default("expected '\\n' after '\\r', saw EOF"sv);
13212
13213 if TOML_UNLIKELY(*cp != U'\n')
13214 set_error_and_return_default("expected '\\n' after '\\r', saw '"sv,
13215 escaped_codepoint{ *cp },
13216 "'"sv);
13217 }
13218 else if (*cp != U'\n')
13219 return false;
13220
13221 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip \n
13222 return true;
13223 }
13224
13225 bool consume_rest_of_line()
13226 {
13227 return_if_error_or_eof({});
13228
13229 do
13230 {
13231 if (is_ascii_vertical_whitespace(*cp))
13232 return consume_line_break();
13233 else
13234 advance();
13235 return_if_error({});
13236 }
13237 while (!is_eof());
13238
13239 return true;
13240 }
13241
13242 bool consume_comment()
13243 {
13244 return_if_error_or_eof({});
13245
13246 if (*cp != U'#')
13247 return false;
13248
13249 push_parse_scope("comment"sv);
13250
13251 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the '#'
13252
13253 while (!is_eof())
13254 {
13255 if (consume_line_break())
13256 return true;
13257 return_if_error({});
13258
13259#if TOML_LANG_AT_LEAST(1, 0, 0)
13260
13261 // toml/issues/567 (disallow non-TAB control characters in comments)
13262 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_nontab_control_character(*cp))
13263 set_error_and_return_default(
13264 "control characters other than TAB (U+0009) are explicitly prohibited in comments"sv);
13265
13266 // toml/pull/720 (disallow surrogates in comments)
13267 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_unicode_surrogate(*cp))
13268 set_error_and_return_default(
13269 "unicode surrogates (U+D800 to U+DFFF) are explicitly prohibited in comments"sv);
13270#endif
13271
13272 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13273 }
13274
13275 return true;
13276 }
13277
13278 TOML_NODISCARD
13279 bool consume_expected_sequence(std::u32string_view seq)
13280 {
13281 return_if_error({});
13282 TOML_ASSERT(!seq.empty());
13283
13284 for (auto c : seq)
13285 {
13286 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13287 if (*cp != c)
13288 return false;
13289 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13290 }
13291 return true;
13292 }
13293
13294 template <typename T>
13295 TOML_NODISCARD
13296 bool consume_digit_sequence(T* digits, size_t len)
13297 {
13298 return_if_error({});
13299 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(digits);
13300 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(len);
13301
13302 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++)
13303 {
13304 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13305 if (!is_decimal_digit(*cp))
13306 return false;
13307
13308 digits[i] = static_cast<T>(*cp - U'0');
13309 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13310 }
13311 return true;
13312 }
13313
13314 template <typename T>
13315 TOML_NODISCARD
13316 size_t consume_variable_length_digit_sequence(T* buffer, size_t max_len)
13317 {
13318 return_if_error({});
13319 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(buffer);
13320 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(max_len);
13321
13322 size_t i = {};
13323 for (; i < max_len; i++)
13324 {
13325 if (is_eof() || !is_decimal_digit(*cp))
13326 break;
13327
13328 buffer[i] = static_cast<T>(*cp - U'0');
13329 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13330 }
13331 return i;
13332 }
13333
13334 TOML_NODISCARD
13335 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13336 std::string_view parse_basic_string(bool multi_line)
13337 {
13338 return_if_error({});
13339 assert_not_eof();
13340 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'"');
13341 push_parse_scope("string"sv);
13342
13343 // skip the '"'
13344 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13345
13346 // multi-line strings ignore a single line ending right at the beginning
13347 if (multi_line)
13348 {
13349 consume_line_break();
13350 return_if_error({});
13351 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13352 }
13353
13354 auto& str = string_buffer;
13355 str.clear();
13356 bool escaped = false;
13357 bool skipping_whitespace = false;
13358 do
13359 {
13360 if (escaped)
13361 {
13362 escaped = false;
13363
13364 // handle 'line ending slashes' in multi-line mode
13365 if (multi_line && is_whitespace(*cp))
13366 {
13367 consume_leading_whitespace();
13368
13369 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!consume_line_break())
13370 set_error_and_return_default(
13371 "line-ending backslashes must be the last non-whitespace character on the line"sv);
13372
13373 skipping_whitespace = true;
13374 return_if_error({});
13375 continue;
13376 }
13377
13378 bool skip_escaped_codepoint = true;
13379 assert_not_eof();
13380 switch (const auto escaped_codepoint = *cp)
13381 {
13382 // 'regular' escape codes
13383 case U'b': str += '\b'; break;
13384 case U'f': str += '\f'; break;
13385 case U'n': str += '\n'; break;
13386 case U'r': str += '\r'; break;
13387 case U't': str += '\t'; break;
13388 case U'"': str += '"'; break;
13389 case U'\\': str += '\\'; break;
13390
13391#if TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED // toml/pull/790 (\e shorthand for \x1B)
13392 case U'e': str += '\x1B'; break;
13393#else
13394 case U'e':
13395 set_error_and_return_default(
13396 "escape sequence '\\e' is not supported in TOML 1.0.0 and earlier"sv);
13397#endif
13398
13399#if TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED // toml/pull/796 (\xHH unicode scalar sequences)
13400 case U'x': [[fallthrough]];
13401#else
13402 case U'x':
13403 set_error_and_return_default(
13404 "escape sequence '\\x' is not supported in TOML 1.0.0 and earlier"sv);
13405#endif
13406
13407 // unicode scalar sequences
13408 case U'u': [[fallthrough]];
13409 case U'U':
13410 {
13411 push_parse_scope("unicode scalar sequence"sv);
13412 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13413 skip_escaped_codepoint = false;
13414
13415 uint32_t place_value =
13416 escaped_codepoint == U'U' ? 0x10000000u : (escaped_codepoint == U'u' ? 0x1000u : 0x10u);
13417 uint32_t sequence_value{};
13418 while (place_value)
13419 {
13420 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13421
13422 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!is_hexadecimal_digit(*cp))
13423 set_error_and_return_default("expected hex digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13424
13425 sequence_value += place_value * hex_to_dec(*cp);
13426 place_value /= 16u;
13427 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13428 }
13429
13430 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_unicode_surrogate(sequence_value))
13431 set_error_and_return_default(
13432 "unicode surrogates (U+D800 - U+DFFF) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13433 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(sequence_value > 0x10FFFFu)
13434 set_error_and_return_default("values greater than U+10FFFF are invalid"sv);
13435
13436 if (sequence_value < 0x80)
13437 {
13438 str += static_cast<char>(sequence_value);
13439 }
13440 else if (sequence_value < 0x800u)
13441 {
13442 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value >> 6) | 0xC0u);
13443 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13444 }
13445 else if (sequence_value < 0x10000u)
13446 {
13447 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value >> 12) | 0xE0u);
13448 str += static_cast<char>(((sequence_value >> 6) & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13449 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13450 }
13451 else if (sequence_value < 0x110000u)
13452 {
13453 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value >> 18) | 0xF0u);
13454 str += static_cast<char>(((sequence_value >> 12) & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13455 str += static_cast<char>(((sequence_value >> 6) & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13456 str += static_cast<char>((sequence_value & 0x3Fu) | 0x80u);
13457 }
13458 break;
13459 }
13460
13461 // ???
13462 TOML_UNLIKELY_CASE
13463 default: set_error_and_return_default("unknown escape sequence '\\"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13464 }
13465
13466 if (skip_escaped_codepoint)
13467 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13468 }
13469 else
13470 {
13471 // handle closing delimiters
13472 if (*cp == U'"')
13473 {
13474 if (multi_line)
13475 {
13476 size_t lookaheads = {};
13477 size_t consecutive_delimiters = 1;
13478 do
13479 {
13480 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13481 lookaheads++;
13482 if (!is_eof() && *cp == U'"')
13483 consecutive_delimiters++;
13484 else
13485 break;
13486 }
13487 while (lookaheads < 4u);
13488
13489 switch (consecutive_delimiters)
13490 {
13491 // """ " (one quote somewhere in a ML string)
13492 case 1:
13493 str += '"';
13494 skipping_whitespace = false;
13495 continue;
13496
13497 // """ "" (two quotes somewhere in a ML string)
13498 case 2:
13499 str.append("\"\""sv);
13500 skipping_whitespace = false;
13501 continue;
13502
13503 // """ """ (the end of the string)
13504 case 3: return str;
13505
13506 // """ """" (one at the end of the string)
13507 case 4: str += '"'; return str;
13508
13509 // """ """"" (two quotes at the end of the string)
13510 case 5:
13511 str.append("\"\""sv);
13512 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the last '"'
13513 return str;
13514
13515 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
13516 }
13517 }
13518 else
13519 {
13520 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the closing delimiter
13521 return str;
13522 }
13523 }
13524
13525 // handle escapes
13526 else if (*cp == U'\\')
13527 {
13528 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({}); // skip the '\'
13529 skipping_whitespace = false;
13530 escaped = true;
13531 continue;
13532 }
13533
13534 // handle line endings in multi-line mode
13535 if (multi_line && is_ascii_vertical_whitespace(*cp))
13536 {
13537 consume_line_break();
13538 return_if_error({});
13539 if (!skipping_whitespace)
13540 str += '\n';
13541 continue;
13542 }
13543
13544 // handle control characters
13545 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_nontab_control_character(*cp))
13546 set_error_and_return_default(
13547 "unescaped control characters other than TAB (U+0009) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13548
13549#if TOML_LANG_AT_LEAST(1, 0, 0)
13550
13551 // handle surrogates in strings
13552 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_unicode_surrogate(*cp))
13553 set_error_and_return_default(
13554 "unescaped unicode surrogates (U+D800 to U+DFFF) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13555#endif
13556
13557 if (multi_line)
13558 {
13559 if (!skipping_whitespace || !is_horizontal_whitespace(*cp))
13560 {
13561 skipping_whitespace = false;
13562 str.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13563 }
13564 }
13565 else
13566 str.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13567
13568 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13569 }
13570 }
13571 while (!is_eof());
13572
13573 set_error_and_return_default("encountered end-of-file"sv);
13574 }
13575
13576 TOML_NODISCARD
13577 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13578 std::string_view parse_literal_string(bool multi_line)
13579 {
13580 return_if_error({});
13581 assert_not_eof();
13582 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'\'');
13583 push_parse_scope("literal string"sv);
13584
13585 // skip the delimiter
13586 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13587
13588 // multi-line strings ignore a single line ending right at the beginning
13589 if (multi_line)
13590 {
13591 consume_line_break();
13592 return_if_error({});
13593 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13594 }
13595
13596 auto& str = string_buffer;
13597 str.clear();
13598 do
13599 {
13600 return_if_error({});
13601
13602 // handle closing delimiters
13603 if (*cp == U'\'')
13604 {
13605 if (multi_line)
13606 {
13607 size_t lookaheads = {};
13608 size_t consecutive_delimiters = 1;
13609 do
13610 {
13611 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13612 lookaheads++;
13613 if (!is_eof() && *cp == U'\'')
13614 consecutive_delimiters++;
13615 else
13616 break;
13617 }
13618 while (lookaheads < 4u);
13619
13620 switch (consecutive_delimiters)
13621 {
13622 // ''' ' (one quote somewhere in a ML string)
13623 case 1: str += '\''; continue;
13624
13625 // ''' '' (two quotes somewhere in a ML string)
13626 case 2: str.append("''"sv); continue;
13627
13628 // ''' ''' (the end of the string)
13629 case 3: return str;
13630
13631 // ''' '''' (one at the end of the string)
13632 case 4: str += '\''; return str;
13633
13634 // ''' ''''' (two quotes at the end of the string)
13635 case 5:
13636 str.append("''"sv);
13637 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the last '
13638 return str;
13639
13640 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
13641 }
13642 }
13643 else
13644 {
13645 advance_and_return_if_error({}); // skip the closing delimiter
13646 return str;
13647 }
13648 }
13649
13650 // handle line endings in multi-line mode
13651 if (multi_line && is_ascii_vertical_whitespace(*cp))
13652 {
13653 consume_line_break();
13654 return_if_error({});
13655 str += '\n';
13656 continue;
13657 }
13658
13659 // handle control characters
13660 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_nontab_control_character(*cp))
13661 set_error_and_return_default(
13662 "control characters other than TAB (U+0009) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13663
13664#if TOML_LANG_AT_LEAST(1, 0, 0)
13665
13666 // handle surrogates in strings
13667 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_unicode_surrogate(*cp))
13668 set_error_and_return_default("unicode surrogates (U+D800 - U+DFFF) are explicitly prohibited"sv);
13669#endif
13670
13671 str.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13672 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13673 }
13674 while (!is_eof());
13675
13676 set_error_and_return_default("encountered end-of-file"sv);
13677 }
13678
13679 TOML_NODISCARD
13680 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13681 parsed_string parse_string()
13682 {
13683 return_if_error({});
13684 assert_not_eof();
13685 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_string_delimiter(*cp));
13686 push_parse_scope("string"sv);
13687
13688 // get the first three characters to determine the string type
13689 const auto first = cp->value;
13690 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13691 const auto second = cp->value;
13692 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13693 const auto third = cp ? cp->value : U'\0';
13694
13695 // if we were eof at the third character then first and second need to be
13696 // the same string character (otherwise it's an unterminated string)
13697 if (is_eof())
13698 {
13699 if (second == first)
13700 return {};
13701
13702 set_error_and_return_default("encountered end-of-file"sv);
13703 }
13704
13705 // if the first three characters are all the same string delimiter then
13706 // it's a multi-line string.
13707 else if (first == second && first == third)
13708 {
13709 return { first == U'\'' ? parse_literal_string(true) : parse_basic_string(true), true };
13710 }
13711
13712 // otherwise it's just a regular string.
13713 else
13714 {
13715 // step back two characters so that the current
13716 // character is the string delimiter
13717 go_back(2u);
13718
13719 return { first == U'\'' ? parse_literal_string(false) : parse_basic_string(false), false };
13720 }
13721 }
13722
13723 TOML_NODISCARD
13724 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13725 std::string_view parse_bare_key_segment()
13726 {
13727 return_if_error({});
13728 assert_not_eof();
13729 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_bare_key_character(*cp));
13730
13731 string_buffer.clear();
13732
13733 while (!is_eof())
13734 {
13735 if (!is_bare_key_character(*cp))
13736 break;
13737
13738 string_buffer.append(cp->bytes, cp->count);
13739 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13740 }
13741
13742 return string_buffer;
13743 }
13744
13745 TOML_NODISCARD
13746 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13747 bool parse_boolean()
13748 {
13749 return_if_error({});
13750 assert_not_eof();
13751 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_match(*cp, U't', U'f', U'T', U'F'));
13752 push_parse_scope("boolean"sv);
13753
13754 start_recording(true);
13755 auto result = is_match(*cp, U't', U'T');
13756 if (!consume_expected_sequence(result ? U"true"sv : U"false"sv))
13757 set_error_and_return_default("expected '"sv,
13758 to_sv(result),
13759 "', saw '"sv,
13760 to_sv(recording_buffer),
13761 "'"sv);
13762 stop_recording();
13763
13764 if (cp && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
13765 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13766
13767 return result;
13768 }
13769
13770 TOML_NODISCARD
13771 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13772 double parse_inf_or_nan()
13773 {
13774 return_if_error({});
13775 assert_not_eof();
13776 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_match(*cp, U'i', U'n', U'I', U'N', U'+', U'-'));
13777 push_parse_scope("floating-point"sv);
13778
13779 start_recording(true);
13780 const bool negative = *cp == U'-';
13781 if (negative || *cp == U'+')
13782 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13783
13784 const bool inf = is_match(*cp, U'i', U'I');
13785 if (!consume_expected_sequence(inf ? U"inf"sv : U"nan"sv))
13786 set_error_and_return_default("expected '"sv,
13787 inf ? "inf"sv : "nan"sv,
13788 "', saw '"sv,
13789 to_sv(recording_buffer),
13790 "'"sv);
13791 stop_recording();
13792
13793 if (cp && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
13794 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13795
13796 return inf ? (negative ? -std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity() : std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity())
13797 : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
13798 }
13799
13800 TOML_NODISCARD
13801 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13802 double parse_float()
13803 {
13804 return_if_error({});
13805 assert_not_eof();
13806 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-', U'.') || is_decimal_digit(*cp));
13807 push_parse_scope("floating-point"sv);
13808
13809 // sign
13810 const int sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
13811 if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
13812 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13813
13814 // consume value chars
13815 char chars[utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length];
13816 size_t length = {};
13817 const utf8_codepoint* prev = {};
13818 bool seen_decimal = false, seen_exponent = false;
13819 char first_integer_part = '\0';
13820 while (!is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
13821 {
13822 if (*cp == U'_')
13823 {
13824 if (!prev || !is_decimal_digit(*prev))
13825 set_error_and_return_default("underscores may only follow digits"sv);
13826
13827 prev = cp;
13828 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13829 continue;
13830 }
13831 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(prev && *prev == U'_' && !is_decimal_digit(*cp))
13832 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
13833 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(length == sizeof(chars))
13834 set_error_and_return_default("exceeds length limit of "sv,
13835 sizeof(chars),
13836 " digits"sv,
13837 (seen_exponent ? ""sv : " (consider using exponent notation)"sv));
13838 else if (*cp == U'.')
13839 {
13840 // .1
13841 // -.1
13842 // +.1 (no integer part)
13843 if (!first_integer_part)
13844 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '.'"sv);
13845
13846 // 1.0e+.10 (exponent cannot have '.')
13847 else if (seen_exponent)
13848 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent decimal digit or sign, saw '.'"sv);
13849
13850 // 1.0.e+.10
13851 // 1..0
13852 // (multiple '.')
13853 else if (seen_decimal)
13854 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit or exponent, saw '.'"sv);
13855
13856 seen_decimal = true;
13857 }
13858 else if (is_match(*cp, U'e', U'E'))
13859 {
13860 if (prev && !is_decimal_digit(*prev))
13861 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13862
13863 // 1.0ee+10 (multiple 'e')
13864 else if (seen_exponent)
13865 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13866
13867 seen_decimal = true; // implied
13868 seen_exponent = true;
13869 }
13870 else if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
13871 {
13872 // 1.-0 (sign in mantissa)
13873 if (!seen_exponent)
13874 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit or '.', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13875
13876 // 1.0e1-0 (misplaced exponent sign)
13877 else if (!is_match(*prev, U'e', U'E'))
13878 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13879 }
13880 else if (is_decimal_digit(*cp))
13881 {
13882 if (!seen_decimal)
13883 {
13884 if (!first_integer_part)
13885 first_integer_part = static_cast<char>(cp->bytes[0]);
13886 else if (first_integer_part == '0')
13887 set_error_and_return_default("leading zeroes are prohibited"sv);
13888 }
13889 }
13890 else
13891 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13892
13893 chars[length++] = static_cast<char>(cp->bytes[0]);
13894 prev = cp;
13895 advance_and_return_if_error({});
13896 }
13897
13898 // sanity-check ending state
13899 if (prev)
13900 {
13901 if (*prev == U'_')
13902 {
13903 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13904 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
13905 }
13906 else if (is_match(*prev, U'e', U'E', U'+', U'-', U'.'))
13907 {
13908 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
13909 set_error_and_return_default("expected decimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13910 }
13911 }
13912
13913 // convert to double
13914 double result;
13915#if TOML_FLOAT_CHARCONV
13916 {
13917 auto fc_result = std::from_chars(chars, chars + length, result);
13918 switch (fc_result.ec)
13919 {
13920 TOML_LIKELY_CASE
13921 case std::errc{}: // ok
13922 return result * sign;
13923
13924 case std::errc::invalid_argument:
13925 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
13926 std::string_view{ chars, length },
13927 "' could not be interpreted as a value"sv);
13928 break;
13929
13930 case std::errc::result_out_of_range:
13931 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
13932 std::string_view{ chars, length },
13933 "' is not representable in 64 bits"sv);
13934 break;
13935
13936 default: //??
13937 set_error_and_return_default("an unspecified error occurred while trying to interpret '"sv,
13938 std::string_view{ chars, length },
13939 "' as a value"sv);
13940 }
13941 }
13942#else
13943 {
13944 std::stringstream ss;
13945 ss.imbue(std::locale::classic());
13946 ss.write(chars, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
13947 if ((ss >> result))
13948 return result * sign;
13949 else
13950 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
13951 std::string_view{ chars, length },
13952 "' could not be interpreted as a value"sv);
13953 }
13954#endif
13955 }
13956
13957 TOML_NODISCARD
13958 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
13959 double parse_hex_float()
13960 {
13961 return_if_error({});
13962 assert_not_eof();
13963 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_match(*cp, U'0', U'+', U'-'));
13964 push_parse_scope("hexadecimal floating-point"sv);
13965
13966#if TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED // toml/issues/562 (hexfloats)
13967
13968 // sign
13969 const int sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
13970 if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
13971 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13972
13973 // '0'
13974 if (*cp != U'0')
13975 set_error_and_return_default(" expected '0', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13976 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13977
13978 // 'x' or 'X'
13979 if (!is_match(*cp, U'x', U'X'))
13980 set_error_and_return_default("expected 'x' or 'X', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
13981 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
13982
13983 // <HEX DIGITS> ([.]<HEX DIGITS>)? [pP] [+-]? <DEC DIGITS>
13984
13985 // consume value fragments
13986 struct fragment
13987 {
13988 char chars[24];
13989 size_t length;
13990 double value;
13991 };
13992 fragment fragments[] = {
13993 {}, // mantissa, whole part
13994 {}, // mantissa, fractional part
13995 {} // exponent
13996 };
13997 fragment* current_fragment = fragments;
13998 const utf8_codepoint* prev = {};
13999 int exponent_sign = 1;
14000 while (!is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14001 {
14002 if (*cp == U'_')
14003 {
14004 if (!prev || !is_hexadecimal_digit(*prev))
14005 set_error_and_return_default("underscores may only follow digits"sv);
14006
14007 prev = cp;
14008 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14009 continue;
14010 }
14011 else if (prev && *prev == U'_' && !is_hexadecimal_digit(*cp))
14012 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
14013 else if (*cp == U'.')
14014 {
14015 // 0x10.0p-.0 (exponent cannot have '.')
14016 if (current_fragment == fragments + 2)
14017 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit or sign, saw '.'"sv);
14018
14019 // 0x10.0.p-0 (multiple '.')
14020 else if (current_fragment == fragments + 1)
14021 set_error_and_return_default("expected hexadecimal digit or exponent, saw '.'"sv);
14022
14023 else
14024 current_fragment++;
14025 }
14026 else if (is_match(*cp, U'p', U'P'))
14027 {
14028 // 0x10.0pp-0 (multiple 'p')
14029 if (current_fragment == fragments + 2)
14030 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit or sign, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14031
14032 // 0x.p-0 (mantissa is just '.')
14033 else if (fragments[0].length == 0u && fragments[1].length == 0u)
14034 set_error_and_return_default("expected hexadecimal digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14035
14036 else
14037 current_fragment = fragments + 2;
14038 }
14039 else if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
14040 {
14041 // 0x-10.0p-0 (sign in mantissa)
14042 if (current_fragment != fragments + 2)
14043 set_error_and_return_default("expected hexadecimal digit or '.', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14044
14045 // 0x10.0p0- (misplaced exponent sign)
14046 else if (!is_match(*prev, U'p', U'P'))
14047 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14048
14049 else
14050 exponent_sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
14051 }
14052 else if (current_fragment < fragments + 2 && !is_hexadecimal_digit(*cp))
14053 set_error_and_return_default("expected hexadecimal digit or '.', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14054 else if (current_fragment == fragments + 2 && !is_decimal_digit(*cp))
14055 set_error_and_return_default("expected exponent digit or sign, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14056 else if (current_fragment->length == sizeof(fragment::chars))
14057 set_error_and_return_default("fragment exceeeds maximum length of "sv,
14058 sizeof(fragment::chars),
14059 " characters"sv);
14060 else
14061 current_fragment->chars[current_fragment->length++] = static_cast<char>(cp->bytes[0]);
14062
14063 prev = cp;
14064 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14065 }
14066
14067 // sanity-check ending state
14068 if (current_fragment != fragments + 2 || current_fragment->length == 0u)
14069 {
14070 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14071 set_error_and_return_default("missing exponent"sv);
14072 }
14073 else if (prev && *prev == U'_')
14074 {
14075 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14076 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
14077 }
14078
14079 // calculate values for the three fragments
14080 for (int fragment_idx = 0; fragment_idx < 3; fragment_idx++)
14081 {
14082 auto& f = fragments[fragment_idx];
14083 const uint32_t base = fragment_idx == 2 ? 10u : 16u;
14084
14085 // left-trim zeroes
14086 const char* c = f.chars;
14087 size_t sig = {};
14088 while (f.length && *c == '0')
14089 {
14090 f.length--;
14091 c++;
14092 sig++;
14093 }
14094 if (!f.length)
14095 continue;
14096
14097 // calculate value
14098 auto place = 1u;
14099 for (size_t i = 0; i < f.length - 1u; i++)
14100 place *= base;
14101 uint32_t val{};
14102 while (place)
14103 {
14104 if (base == 16)
14105 val += place * hex_to_dec(*c);
14106 else
14107 val += place * static_cast<uint32_t>(*c - '0');
14108 if (fragment_idx == 1)
14109 sig++;
14110 c++;
14111 place /= base;
14112 }
14113 f.value = static_cast<double>(val);
14114
14115 // shift the fractional part
14116 if (fragment_idx == 1)
14117 {
14118 while (sig--)
14119 f.value /= base;
14120 }
14121 }
14122
14123 return (fragments[0].value + fragments[1].value) * pow(2.0, fragments[2].value * exponent_sign) * sign;
14124
14125#else // !TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED
14126
14127 set_error_and_return_default("hexadecimal floating-point values are not supported "
14128 "in TOML 1.0.0 and earlier"sv);
14129
14130#endif // !TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED
14131 }
14132
14133 template <uint64_t base>
14134 TOML_NODISCARD
14135 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
14136 int64_t parse_integer()
14137 {
14138 return_if_error({});
14139 assert_not_eof();
14140 using traits = parse_integer_traits<base>;
14141 push_parse_scope(traits::scope_qualifier);
14142
14143 [[maybe_unused]] int64_t sign = 1;
14144 if constexpr (traits::is_signed)
14145 {
14146 sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
14147 if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
14148 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14149 }
14150
14151 if constexpr (base == 10)
14152 {
14153 if (!traits::is_digit(*cp))
14154 set_error_and_return_default("expected expected digit or sign, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14155 }
14156 else
14157 {
14158 // '0'
14159 if (*cp != U'0')
14160 set_error_and_return_default("expected '0', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14161 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14162
14163 // 'b', 'o', 'x'
14164 if (*cp != traits::prefix_codepoint)
14165 set_error_and_return_default("expected '"sv, traits::prefix, "', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14166 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14167
14168 if (!traits::is_digit(*cp))
14169 set_error_and_return_default("expected digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14170 }
14171
14172 // consume digits
14173 char digits[utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length];
14174 size_t length = {};
14175 const utf8_codepoint* prev = {};
14176 while (!is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14177 {
14178 if (*cp == U'_')
14179 {
14180 if (!prev || !traits::is_digit(*prev))
14181 set_error_and_return_default("underscores may only follow digits"sv);
14182
14183 prev = cp;
14184 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14185 continue;
14186 }
14187 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(prev && *prev == U'_' && !traits::is_digit(*cp))
14188 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
14189 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(!traits::is_digit(*cp))
14190 set_error_and_return_default("expected digit, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14191 else if TOML_UNLIKELY(length == sizeof(digits))
14192 set_error_and_return_default("exceeds length limit of "sv, sizeof(digits), " digits"sv);
14193 else
14194 digits[length++] = static_cast<char>(cp->bytes[0]);
14195
14196 prev = cp;
14197 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14198 }
14199
14200 // sanity check ending state
14201 if (prev && *prev == U'_')
14202 {
14203 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14204 set_error_and_return_default("underscores must be followed by digits"sv);
14205 }
14206
14207 // single digits can be converted trivially
14208 if (length == 1u)
14209 {
14210 int64_t result;
14211
14212 if constexpr (base == 16)
14213 result = static_cast<int64_t>(hex_to_dec(digits[0]));
14214 else
14215 result = static_cast<int64_t>(digits[0] - '0');
14216
14217 if constexpr (traits::is_signed)
14218 result *= sign;
14219
14220 return result;
14221 }
14222
14223 // bin, oct and hex allow leading zeroes so trim them first
14224 const char* end = digits + length;
14225 const char* msd = digits;
14226 if constexpr (base != 10)
14227 {
14228 while (msd < end && *msd == '0')
14229 msd++;
14230 if (msd == end)
14231 return 0ll;
14232 }
14233
14234 // decimal integers do not allow leading zeroes
14235 else
14236 {
14237 if TOML_UNLIKELY(digits[0] == '0')
14238 set_error_and_return_default("leading zeroes are prohibited"sv);
14239 }
14240
14241 // range check
14242 if TOML_UNLIKELY(static_cast<size_t>(end - msd) > traits::max_digits)
14243 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
14244 traits::full_prefix,
14245 std::string_view{ digits, length },
14246 "' is not representable in 64 bits"sv);
14247
14248 // do the thing
14249 {
14250 uint64_t result = {};
14251 {
14252 uint64_t power = 1;
14253 while (--end >= msd)
14254 {
14255 if constexpr (base == 16)
14256 result += power * hex_to_dec(*end);
14257 else
14258 result += power * static_cast<uint64_t>(*end - '0');
14259
14260 power *= base;
14261 }
14262 }
14263
14264 // range check
14265 static constexpr auto i64_max = static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)());
14266 if TOML_UNLIKELY(result > i64_max + (sign < 0 ? 1u : 0u))
14267 set_error_and_return_default("'"sv,
14268 traits::full_prefix,
14269 std::string_view{ digits, length },
14270 "' is not representable in 64 bits"sv);
14271
14272 if constexpr (traits::is_signed)
14273 {
14274 // avoid signed multiply UB when parsing INT64_MIN
14275 if TOML_UNLIKELY(sign < 0 && result == i64_max + 1u)
14276 return (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)();
14277
14278 return static_cast<int64_t>(result) * sign;
14279 }
14280 else
14281 return static_cast<int64_t>(result);
14282 }
14283 }
14284
14285 TOML_NODISCARD
14286 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
14287 date parse_date(bool part_of_datetime = false)
14288 {
14289 return_if_error({});
14290 assert_not_eof();
14291 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_decimal_digit(*cp));
14292 push_parse_scope("date"sv);
14293
14294 // "YYYY"
14295 uint32_t digits[4];
14296 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 4u))
14297 set_error_and_return_default("expected 4-digit year, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14298 const auto year = digits[3] + digits[2] * 10u + digits[1] * 100u + digits[0] * 1000u;
14299 const auto is_leap_year = (year % 4u == 0u) && ((year % 100u != 0u) || (year % 400u == 0u));
14300 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14301
14302 // '-'
14303 if (*cp != U'-')
14304 set_error_and_return_default("expected '-', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14305 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14306
14307 // "MM"
14308 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14309 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit month, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14310 const auto month = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14311 if (month == 0u || month > 12u)
14312 set_error_and_return_default("expected month between 1 and 12 (inclusive), saw "sv, month);
14313 const auto max_days_in_month = month == 2u
14314 ? (is_leap_year ? 29u : 28u)
14315 : (month == 4u || month == 6u || month == 9u || month == 11u ? 30u : 31u);
14316 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14317
14318 // '-'
14319 if (*cp != U'-')
14320 set_error_and_return_default("expected '-', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14321 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14322
14323 // "DD"
14324 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14325 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit day, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14326 const auto day = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14327 if (day == 0u || day > max_days_in_month)
14328 set_error_and_return_default("expected day between 1 and "sv,
14329 max_days_in_month,
14330 " (inclusive), saw "sv,
14331 day);
14332
14333 if (!part_of_datetime && !is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14334 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14335
14336 return { year, month, day };
14337 }
14338
14339 TOML_NODISCARD
14340 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
14341 time parse_time(bool part_of_datetime = false)
14342 {
14343 return_if_error({});
14344 assert_not_eof();
14345 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_decimal_digit(*cp));
14346 push_parse_scope("time"sv);
14347
14348 static constexpr size_t max_digits = 64; // far more than necessary but needed to allow fractional
14349 // millisecond truncation per the spec
14350 uint32_t digits[max_digits];
14351
14352 // "HH"
14353 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14354 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit hour, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14355 const auto hour = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14356 if (hour > 23u)
14357 set_error_and_return_default("expected hour between 0 to 59 (inclusive), saw "sv, hour);
14358 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14359
14360 // ':'
14361 if (*cp != U':')
14362 set_error_and_return_default("expected ':', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14363 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14364
14365 // "MM"
14366 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14367 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit minute, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14368 const auto minute = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14369 if (minute > 59u)
14370 set_error_and_return_default("expected minute between 0 and 59 (inclusive), saw "sv, minute);
14371 auto time = toml::time{ hour, minute };
14372
14373 // ':'
14374 if constexpr (TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED) // toml/issues/671 (allow omission of seconds)
14375 {
14376 if (is_eof() || is_value_terminator(*cp) || (part_of_datetime && is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-', U'Z', U'z')))
14377 return time;
14378 }
14379 else
14380 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14381 if (*cp != U':')
14382 set_error_and_return_default("expected ':', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14383 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14384
14385 // "SS"
14386 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14387 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit second, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14388 const auto second = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10u;
14389 if (second > 59u)
14390 set_error_and_return_default("expected second between 0 and 59 (inclusive), saw "sv, second);
14391 time.second = static_cast<decltype(time.second)>(second);
14392
14393 // '.' (early-exiting is allowed; fractional is optional)
14394 if (is_eof() || is_value_terminator(*cp) || (part_of_datetime && is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-', U'Z', U'z')))
14395 return time;
14396 if (*cp != U'.')
14397 set_error_and_return_default("expected '.', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14398 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14399
14400 // "FFFFFFFFF"
14401 size_t digit_count = consume_variable_length_digit_sequence(digits, max_digits);
14402 if (!digit_count)
14403 {
14404 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14405 set_error_and_return_default("expected fractional digits, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14406 }
14407 else if (!is_eof())
14408 {
14409 if (digit_count == max_digits && is_decimal_digit(*cp))
14410 set_error_and_return_default("fractional component exceeds maximum precision of "sv, max_digits);
14411 else if (!part_of_datetime && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14412 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14413 }
14414 uint32_t value = 0u;
14415 uint32_t place = 1u;
14416 for (auto i = impl::min<size_t>(digit_count, 9u); i-- > 0u;)
14417 {
14418 value += digits[i] * place;
14419 place *= 10u;
14420 }
14421 for (auto i = digit_count; i < 9u; i++) // implicit zeros
14422 value *= 10u;
14423 time.nanosecond = value;
14424 return time;
14425 }
14426
14427 TOML_NODISCARD
14428 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
14429 date_time parse_date_time()
14430 {
14431 return_if_error({});
14432 assert_not_eof();
14433 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_decimal_digit(*cp));
14434 push_parse_scope("date-time"sv);
14435
14436 // "YYYY-MM-DD"
14437 auto date = parse_date(true);
14438 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14439
14440 // ' ', 'T' or 't'
14441 if (!is_match(*cp, U' ', U'T', U't'))
14442 set_error_and_return_default("expected space, 'T' or 't', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14443 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14444
14445 // "HH:MM:SS.FFFFFFFFF"
14446 auto time = parse_time(true);
14447 return_if_error({});
14448
14449 // no offset
14450 if (is_eof() || is_value_terminator(*cp))
14451 return { date, time };
14452
14453 // zero offset ('Z' or 'z')
14454 time_offset offset{};
14455 if (is_match(*cp, U'Z', U'z'))
14456 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14457
14458 // explicit offset ("+/-HH:MM")
14459 else if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
14460 {
14461 push_parse_scope("date-time offset"sv);
14462
14463 // sign
14464 int sign = *cp == U'-' ? -1 : 1;
14465 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14466
14467 // "HH"
14468 int digits[2];
14469 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14470 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit hour, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14471 const auto hour = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10;
14472 if (hour > 23)
14473 set_error_and_return_default("expected hour between 0 and 23 (inclusive), saw "sv, hour);
14474 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
14475
14476 // ':'
14477 if (*cp != U':')
14478 set_error_and_return_default("expected ':', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14479 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
14480
14481 // "MM"
14482 if (!consume_digit_sequence(digits, 2u))
14483 set_error_and_return_default("expected 2-digit minute, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
14484 const auto minute = digits[1] + digits[0] * 10;
14485 if (minute > 59)
14486 set_error_and_return_default("expected minute between 0 and 59 (inclusive), saw "sv, minute);
14487 offset.minutes = static_cast<decltype(offset.minutes)>((hour * 60 + minute) * sign);
14488 }
14489
14490 if (!is_eof() && !is_value_terminator(*cp))
14491 set_error_and_return_default("expected value-terminator, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
14492
14493 return { date, time, offset };
14494 }
14495
14496 TOML_NODISCARD
14497 node_ptr parse_array();
14498
14499 TOML_NODISCARD
14500 node_ptr parse_inline_table();
14501
14502 TOML_NODISCARD
14503 node_ptr parse_value_known_prefixes()
14504 {
14505 return_if_error({});
14506 assert_not_eof();
14507 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!is_control_character(*cp));
14508 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp != U'_');
14509
14510 switch (cp->value)
14511 {
14512 // arrays
14513 case U'[': return parse_array();
14514
