14515 // inline tables
14516 case U'{': return parse_inline_table();
14517
14518 // floats beginning with '.'
14519 case U'.': return node_ptr{ new value{ parse_float() } };
14520
14521 // strings
14522 case U'"': [[fallthrough]];
14523 case U'\'': return node_ptr{ new value{ parse_string().value } };
14524
14525 default:
14526 {
14527 const auto cp_upper = static_cast<uint_least32_t>(cp->value) & ~0x20u;
14528
14529 // bools
14530 if (cp_upper == 70u || cp_upper == 84u) // F or T
14531 return node_ptr{ new value{ parse_boolean() } };
14532
14533 // inf/nan
14534 else if (cp_upper == 73u || cp_upper == 78u) // I or N
14535 return node_ptr{ new value{ parse_inf_or_nan() } };
14536
14537 else
14538 return nullptr;
14539 }
14540 }
14541 TOML_UNREACHABLE;
14542 }
14543
14544 TOML_NODISCARD
14545 node_ptr parse_value()
14546 {
14547 return_if_error({});
14548 assert_not_eof();
14549 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!is_value_terminator(*cp));
14550 push_parse_scope("value"sv);
14551
14552 const depth_counter_scope depth_counter{ nested_values };
14553 if TOML_UNLIKELY(nested_values > max_nested_values)
14554 set_error_and_return_default("exceeded maximum nested value depth of "sv,
14555 max_nested_values,
14556 " (TOML_MAX_NESTED_VALUES)"sv);
14557
14558 // check if it begins with some control character
14559 // (note that this will also fail for whitespace but we're assuming we've
14560 // called consume_leading_whitespace() before calling parse_value())
14561 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_control_character(*cp))
14562 set_error_and_return_default("unexpected control character"sv);
14563
14564 // underscores at the beginning
14565 else if (*cp == U'_')
14566 set_error_and_return_default("values may not begin with underscores"sv);
14567
14568 const auto begin_pos = cp->position;
14569 node_ptr val;
14570
14571 do
14572 {
14573 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!is_control_character(*cp));
14574 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp != U'_');
14575
14576 // detect the value type and parse accordingly,
14577 // starting with value types that can be detected
14578 // unambiguously from just one character.
14579
14580 val = parse_value_known_prefixes();
14581 return_if_error({});
14582 if (val)
14583 break;
14584
14585 // value types from here down require more than one character to unambiguously identify
14586 // so scan ahead and collect a set of value 'traits'.
14587 enum TOML_CLOSED_FLAGS_ENUM value_traits : int
14588 {
14589 has_nothing = 0,
14590 has_digits = 1,
14591 has_b = 1 << 1, // as second char only (0b)
14592 has_e = 1 << 2, // only float exponents
14593 has_o = 1 << 3, // as second char only (0o)
14594 has_p = 1 << 4, // only hexfloat exponents
14595 has_t = 1 << 5,
14596 has_x = 1 << 6, // as second or third char only (0x, -0x, +0x)
14597 has_z = 1 << 7,
14598 has_colon = 1 << 8,
14599 has_plus = 1 << 9,
14600 has_minus = 1 << 10,
14601 has_dot = 1 << 11,
14602 begins_sign = 1 << 12,
14603 begins_digit = 1 << 13,
14604 begins_zero = 1 << 14,
14605 signs_msk = has_plus | has_minus,
14606 bdigit_msk = has_digits | begins_digit,
14607 bzero_msk = bdigit_msk | begins_zero,
14608 };
14609 value_traits traits = has_nothing;
14610 const auto has_any = [&](auto t) noexcept { return (traits & t) != has_nothing; };
14611 const auto has_none = [&](auto t) noexcept { return (traits & t) == has_nothing; };
14612 const auto add_trait = [&](auto t) noexcept { traits = static_cast<value_traits>(traits | t); };
14613
14614 // examine the first character to get the 'begins with' traits
14615 // (good fail-fast opportunity; all the remaining types begin with numeric digits or signs)
14616 if (is_decimal_digit(*cp))
14617 {
14618 add_trait(begins_digit);
14619 if (*cp == U'0')
14620 add_trait(begins_zero);
14621 }
14622 else if (is_match(*cp, U'+', U'-'))
14623 add_trait(begins_sign);
14624 else
14625 break;
14626
14627 // scan the rest of the value to determine the remaining traits
14628 char32_t chars[utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length];
14629 size_t char_count = {}, advance_count = {};
14630 bool eof_while_scanning = false;
14631 const auto scan = [&]() noexcept(!TOML_COMPILER_HAS_EXCEPTIONS)
14632 {
14633 if (is_eof())
14634 return;
14635 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(!is_value_terminator(*cp));
14636
14637 do
14638 {
14639 if (const auto c = **cp; c != U'_')
14640 {
14641 chars[char_count++] = c;
14642
14643 if (is_decimal_digit(c))
14644 add_trait(has_digits);
14645 else if (is_ascii_letter(c))
14646 {
14647 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME((c >= U'a' && c <= U'z') || (c >= U'A' && c <= U'Z'));
14648 switch (static_cast<char32_t>(c | 32u))
14649 {
14650 case U'b':
14651 if (char_count == 2u && has_any(begins_zero))
14652 add_trait(has_b);
14653 break;
14654
14655 case U'e':
14656 if (char_count > 1u
14657 && has_none(has_b | has_o | has_p | has_t | has_x | has_z | has_colon)
14658 && (has_none(has_plus | has_minus) || has_any(begins_sign)))
14659 add_trait(has_e);
14660 break;
14661
14662 case U'o':
14663 if (char_count == 2u && has_any(begins_zero))
14664 add_trait(has_o);
14665 break;
14666
14667 case U'p':
14668 if (has_any(has_x))
14669 add_trait(has_p);
14670 break;
14671
14672 case U'x':
14673 if ((char_count == 2u && has_any(begins_zero))
14674 || (char_count == 3u && has_any(begins_sign) && chars[1] == U'0'))
14675 add_trait(has_x);
14676 break;
14677
14678 case U't': add_trait(has_t); break;
14679 case U'z': add_trait(has_z); break;
14680 }
14681 }
14682 else if (c <= U':')
14683 {
14684 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(c < U'0' || c > U'9');
14685 switch (c)
14686 {
14687 case U'+': add_trait(has_plus); break;
14688 case U'-': add_trait(has_minus); break;
14689 case U'.': add_trait(has_dot); break;
14690 case U':': add_trait(has_colon); break;
14691 }
14692 }
14693 }
14694
14695 advance_and_return_if_error();
14696 advance_count++;
14697 eof_while_scanning = is_eof();
14698 }
14699 while (advance_count < (utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length - 1u) && !is_eof()
14700 && !is_value_terminator(*cp));
14701 };
14702 scan();
14703 return_if_error({});
14704
14705 // force further scanning if this could have been a date-time with a space instead of a T
14706 if (char_count == 10u //
14707 && (traits | begins_zero) == (bzero_msk | has_minus) //
14708 && chars[4] == U'-' //
14709 && chars[7] == U'-' //
14710 && !is_eof() //
14711 && *cp == U' ')
14712 {
14713 const auto pre_advance_count = advance_count;
14714 const auto pre_scan_traits = traits;
14715 chars[char_count++] = *cp;
14716 add_trait(has_t);
14717
14718 const auto backpedal = [&]() noexcept
14719 {
14720 go_back(advance_count - pre_advance_count);
14721 advance_count = pre_advance_count;
14722 traits = pre_scan_traits;
14723 char_count = 10u;
14724 };
14725
14726 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14727 advance_count++;
14728
14729 if (is_eof() || !is_decimal_digit(*cp))
14730 backpedal();
14731 else
14732 {
14733 chars[char_count++] = *cp;
14734
14735 advance_and_return_if_error({});
14736 advance_count++;
14737
14738 scan();
14739 return_if_error({});
14740
14741 if (char_count == 12u)
14742 backpedal();
14743 }
14744 }
14745
14746 // set the reader back to where we started
14747 go_back(advance_count);
14748
14749 // if after scanning ahead we still only have one value character,
14750 // the only valid value type is an integer.
14751 if (char_count == 1u)
14752 {
14753 if (has_any(begins_digit))
14754 {
14755 val.reset(new value{ static_cast<int64_t>(chars[0] - U'0') });
14756 advance(); // skip the digit
14757 break;
14758 }
14759
14760 // anything else would be ambiguous.
14761 else
14762 set_error_and_return_default(eof_while_scanning ? "encountered end-of-file"sv
14763 : "could not determine value type"sv);
14764 }
14765
14766 // now things that can be identified from two or more characters
14767 return_if_error({});
14768 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(char_count >= 2u);
14769
14770 // do some 'fuzzy matching' where there's no ambiguity, since that allows the specific
14771 // typed parse functions to take over and show better diagnostics if there's an issue
14772 // (as opposed to the fallback "could not determine type" message)
14773 if (has_any(has_p))
14774 val.reset(new value{ parse_hex_float() });
14775 else if (has_any(has_x | has_o | has_b))
14776 {
14777 int64_t i;
14778 value_flags flags;
14779 if (has_any(has_x))
14780 {
14781 i = parse_integer<16>();
14782 flags = value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal;
14783 }
14784 else if (has_any(has_o))
14785 {
14786 i = parse_integer<8>();
14787 flags = value_flags::format_as_octal;
14788 }
14789 else // has_b
14790 {
14791 i = parse_integer<2>();
14792 flags = value_flags::format_as_binary;
14793 }
14794 return_if_error({});
14795
14796 val.reset(new value{ i });
14797 val->ref_cast<int64_t>().flags(flags);
14798 }
14799 else if (has_any(has_e) || (has_any(begins_digit) && chars[1] == U'.'))
14800 val.reset(new value{ parse_float() });
14801 else if (has_any(begins_sign))
14802 {
14803 // single-digit signed integers
14804 if (char_count == 2u && has_any(has_digits))
14805 {
14806 val.reset(new value{ static_cast<int64_t>(chars[1] - U'0') * (chars[0] == U'-' ? -1LL : 1LL) });
14807 advance(); // skip the sign
14808 advance(); // skip the digit
14809 break;
14810 }
14811
14812 // simple signed floats (e.g. +1.0)
14813 if (is_decimal_digit(chars[1]) && chars[2] == U'.')
14814 val.reset(new value{ parse_float() });
14815
14816 // signed infinity or nan
14817 else if (is_match(chars[1], U'i', U'n', U'I', U'N'))
14818 val.reset(new value{ parse_inf_or_nan() });
14819 }
14820
14821 return_if_error({});
14822 if (val)
14823 break;
14824
14825 // match trait masks against what they can match exclusively.
14826 // all correct value parses will come out of this list, so doing this as a switch is likely to
14827 // be a better friend to the optimizer on the success path (failure path can be slow but that
14828 // doesn't matter much).
14829 switch (unwrap_enum(traits))
14830 {
14831 // binary integers
14832 // 0b10
14833 case bzero_msk | has_b:
14834 val.reset(new value{ parse_integer<2>() });
14835 val->ref_cast<int64_t>().flags(value_flags::format_as_binary);
14836 break;
14837
14838 // octal integers
14839 // 0o10
14840 case bzero_msk | has_o:
14841 val.reset(new value{ parse_integer<8>() });
14842 val->ref_cast<int64_t>().flags(value_flags::format_as_octal);
14843 break;
14844
14845 // decimal integers
14846 // 00
14847 // 10
14848 // +10
14849 // -10
14850 case bzero_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14851 case bdigit_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14852 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14853 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_plus:
14854 {
14855 // if the value was so long we exhausted the history buffer it's reasonable to assume
14856 // there was more and the value's actual type is impossible to identify without making the
14857 // buffer bigger (since it could have actually been a float), so emit an error.
14858 //
14859 // (this will likely only come up during fuzzing and similar scenarios)
14860 static constexpr size_t max_numeric_value_length =
14861 utf8_buffered_reader::max_history_length - 2u;
14862 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!eof_while_scanning && advance_count > max_numeric_value_length)
14863 set_error_and_return_default("numeric value too long to identify type - cannot exceed "sv,
14864 max_numeric_value_length,
14865 " characters"sv);
14866
14867 val.reset(new value{ parse_integer<10>() });
14868 break;
14869 }
14870
14871 // hexadecimal integers
14872 // 0x10
14873 case bzero_msk | has_x:
14874 val.reset(new value{ parse_integer<16>() });
14875 val->ref_cast<int64_t>().flags(value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal);
14876 break;
14877
14878 // decimal floats
14879 // 0e1
14880 // 0e-1
14881 // 0e+1
14882 // 0.0
14883 // 0.0e1
14884 // 0.0e-1
14885 // 0.0e+1
14886 case bzero_msk | has_e: [[fallthrough]];
14887 case bzero_msk | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14888 case bzero_msk | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14889 case bzero_msk | has_dot: [[fallthrough]];
14890 case bzero_msk | has_dot | has_e: [[fallthrough]];
14891 case bzero_msk | has_dot | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14892 case bzero_msk | has_dot | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14893 // 1e1
14894 // 1e-1
14895 // 1e+1
14896 // 1.0
14897 // 1.0e1
14898 // 1.0e-1
14899 // 1.0e+1
14900 case bdigit_msk | has_e: [[fallthrough]];
14901 case bdigit_msk | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14902 case bdigit_msk | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14903 case bdigit_msk | has_dot: [[fallthrough]];
14904 case bdigit_msk | has_dot | has_e: [[fallthrough]];
14905 case bdigit_msk | has_dot | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14906 case bdigit_msk | has_dot | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14907 // +1e1
14908 // +1.0
14909 // +1.0e1
14910 // +1.0e+1
14911 // +1.0e-1
14912 // -1.0e+1
14913 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14914 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14915 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_e | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14916 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_e | signs_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14917 // -1e1
14918 // -1e+1
14919 // +1e-1
14920 // -1.0
14921 // -1.0e1
14922 // -1.0e-1
14923 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_e | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14924 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_e | signs_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14925 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14926 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_dot | has_e | has_minus:
14927 val.reset(new value{ parse_float() });
14928 break;
14929
14930 // hexadecimal floats
14931 // 0x10p0
14932 // 0x10p-0
14933 // 0x10p+0
14934 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_p: [[fallthrough]];
14935 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_p | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14936 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_p | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14937 // -0x10p0
14938 // -0x10p-0
14939 // +0x10p0
14940 // +0x10p+0
14941 // -0x10p+0
14942 // +0x10p-0
14943 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_p | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14944 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_p | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14945 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_p | signs_msk: [[fallthrough]];
14946 // 0x10.1p0
14947 // 0x10.1p-0
14948 // 0x10.1p+0
14949 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_dot | has_p: [[fallthrough]];
14950 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_dot | has_p | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14951 case bzero_msk | has_x | has_dot | has_p | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14952 // -0x10.1p0
14953 // -0x10.1p-0
14954 // +0x10.1p0
14955 // +0x10.1p+0
14956 // -0x10.1p+0
14957 // +0x10.1p-0
14958 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_dot | has_p | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14959 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_dot | has_p | has_plus: [[fallthrough]];
14960 case begins_sign | has_digits | has_x | has_dot | has_p | signs_msk:
14961 val.reset(new value{ parse_hex_float() });
14962 break;
14963
14964 // times
14965 // HH:MM
14966 // HH:MM:SS
14967 // HH:MM:SS.FFFFFF
14968 case bzero_msk | has_colon: [[fallthrough]];
14969 case bzero_msk | has_colon | has_dot: [[fallthrough]];
14970 case bdigit_msk | has_colon: [[fallthrough]];
14971 case bdigit_msk | has_colon | has_dot: val.reset(new value{ parse_time() }); break;
14972
14973 // local dates
14974 // YYYY-MM-DD
14975 case bzero_msk | has_minus: [[fallthrough]];
14976 case bdigit_msk | has_minus: val.reset(new value{ parse_date() }); break;
14977
14978 // date-times
14979 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM
14980 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM-HH:MM
14981 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM+HH:MM
14982 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM
14983 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM-HH:MM
14984 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM+HH:MM
14985 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS
14986 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS-HH:MM
14987 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+HH:MM
14988 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
14989 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS-HH:MM
14990 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS+HH:MM
14991 case bzero_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14992 case bzero_msk | signs_msk | has_colon | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14993 case bdigit_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14994 case bdigit_msk | signs_msk | has_colon | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
14995 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.FFFFFF
14996 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.FFFFFF-HH:MM
14997 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.FFFFFF+HH:MM
14998 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.FFFFFF
14999 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.FFFFFF-HH:MM
15000 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.FFFFFF+HH:MM
15001 case bzero_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_dot | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15002 case bzero_msk | signs_msk | has_colon | has_dot | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15003 case bdigit_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_dot | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15004 case bdigit_msk | signs_msk | has_colon | has_dot | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15005 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MMZ
15006 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MMZ
15007 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ
15008 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SSZ
15009 // YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.FFFFFFZ
15010 // YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.FFFFFFZ
15011 case bzero_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_z | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15012 case bzero_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_dot | has_z | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15013 case bdigit_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_z | has_t: [[fallthrough]];
15014 case bdigit_msk | has_minus | has_colon | has_dot | has_z | has_t:
15015 val.reset(new value{ parse_date_time() });
15016 break;
15017 }
15018 }
15019 while (false);
15020
15021 if (!val)
15022 {
15023 set_error_at(begin_pos, "could not determine value type"sv);
15024 return_after_error({});
15025 }
15026
15027 val->source_ = { begin_pos, current_position(1), reader.source_path() };
15028 return val;
15029 }
15030
15031 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
15032 bool parse_key()
15033 {
15034 return_if_error({});
15035 assert_not_eof();
15036 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_bare_key_character(*cp) || is_string_delimiter(*cp));
15037 push_parse_scope("key"sv);
15038
15039 key_buffer.clear();
15040 recording_whitespace = false;
15041
15042 while (!is_error())
15043 {
15044 std::string_view key_segment;
15045 const auto key_begin = current_position();
15046
15047 // bare_key_segment
15048 if (is_bare_key_character(*cp))
15049 key_segment = parse_bare_key_segment();
15050
15051 // "quoted key segment"
15052 else if (is_string_delimiter(*cp))
15053 {
15054 const auto begin_pos = cp->position;
15055
15056 recording_whitespace = true;
15057 parsed_string str = parse_string();
15058 recording_whitespace = false;
15059 return_if_error({});
15060
15061 if (str.was_multi_line)
15062 {
15063 set_error_at(begin_pos,
15064 "multi-line strings are prohibited in "sv,
15065 key_buffer.empty() ? ""sv : "dotted "sv,
15066 "keys"sv);
15067 return_after_error({});
15068 }
15069 else
15070 key_segment = str.value;
15071 }
15072
15073 // ???
15074 else
15075 set_error_and_return_default("expected bare key starting character or string delimiter, saw '"sv,
15076 to_sv(*cp),
15077 "'"sv);
15078
15079 const auto key_end = current_position();
15080
15081 // whitespace following the key segment
15082 consume_leading_whitespace();
15083
15084 // store segment
15085 key_buffer.push_back(key_segment, key_begin, key_end);
15086
15087 // eof or no more key to come
15088 if (is_eof() || *cp != U'.')
15089 break;
15090
15091 // was a dotted key - go around again
15092 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15093 consume_leading_whitespace();
15094 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15095 }
15096 return_if_error({});
15097
15098 return true;
15099 }
15100
15101 TOML_NODISCARD
15102 key make_key(size_t segment_index) const
15103 {
15104 TOML_ASSERT(key_buffer.size() > segment_index);
15105
15106 return key{
15107 key_buffer[segment_index],
15108 source_region{ key_buffer.starts[segment_index], key_buffer.ends[segment_index], root.source().path }
15109 };
15110 }
15111
15112 TOML_NODISCARD
15113 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
15114 table* parse_table_header()
15115 {
15116 return_if_error({});
15117 assert_not_eof();
15118 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'[');
15119 push_parse_scope("table header"sv);
15120
15121 const source_position header_begin_pos = cp->position;
15122 source_position header_end_pos;
15123 bool is_arr = false;
15124
15125 // parse header
15126 {
15127 // skip first '['
15128 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15129
15130 // skip past any whitespace that followed the '['
15131 const bool had_leading_whitespace = consume_leading_whitespace();
15132 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15133
15134 // skip second '[' (if present)
15135 if (*cp == U'[')
15136 {
15137 if (had_leading_whitespace)
15138 set_error_and_return_default(
15139 "[[array-of-table]] brackets must be contiguous (i.e. [ [ this ] ] is prohibited)"sv);
15140
15141 is_arr = true;
15142 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15143
15144 // skip past any whitespace that followed the '['
15145 consume_leading_whitespace();
15146 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15147 }
15148
15149 // check for a premature closing ']'
15150 if (*cp == U']')
15151 set_error_and_return_default("tables with blank bare keys are explicitly prohibited"sv);
15152
15153 // get the actual key
15154 start_recording();
15155 parse_key();
15156 stop_recording(1u);
15157 return_if_error({});
15158
15159 // skip past any whitespace that followed the key
15160 consume_leading_whitespace();
15161 return_if_error({});
15162 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15163
15164 // consume the closing ']'
15165 if (*cp != U']')
15166 set_error_and_return_default("expected ']', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15167 if (is_arr)
15168 {
15169 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15170 if (*cp != U']')
15171 set_error_and_return_default("expected ']', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15172 }
15173 advance_and_return_if_error({});
15174 header_end_pos = current_position(1);
15175
15176 // handle the rest of the line after the header
15177 consume_leading_whitespace();
15178 if (!is_eof() && !consume_comment() && !consume_line_break())
15179 set_error_and_return_default("expected a comment or whitespace, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
15180 }
15181 TOML_ASSERT(!key_buffer.empty());
15182
15183 // check if each parent is a table/table array, or can be created implicitly as a table.
15184 table* parent = &root;
15185 for (size_t i = 0, e = key_buffer.size() - 1u; i < e; i++)
15186 {
15187 const std::string_view segment = key_buffer[i];
15188 auto pit = parent->lower_bound(segment);
15189
15190 // parent already existed
15191 if (pit != parent->end() && pit->first == segment)
15192 {
15193 node& p = pit->second;
15194
15195 if (auto tbl = p.as_table())
15196 {
15197 // adding to closed inline tables is illegal
15198 if (tbl->is_inline() && !impl::find(open_inline_tables.begin(), open_inline_tables.end(), tbl))
15199 set_error_and_return_default("cannot insert '"sv,
15200 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15201 "' into existing inline table"sv);
15202
15203 parent = tbl;
15204 }
15205 else if (auto arr = p.as_array(); arr && impl::find(table_arrays.begin(), table_arrays.end(), arr))
15206 {
15207 // table arrays are a special case;
15208 // the spec dictates we select the most recently declared element in the array.
15209 TOML_ASSERT(!arr->empty());
15210 TOML_ASSERT(arr->back().is_table());
15211 parent = &arr->back().ref_cast<table>();
15212 }
15213 else
15214 {
15215 if (!is_arr && p.type() == node_type::table)
15216 set_error_and_return_default("cannot redefine existing table '"sv,
15217 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15218 "'"sv);
15219 else
15220 set_error_and_return_default("cannot redefine existing "sv,
15221 to_sv(p.type()),
15222 " '"sv,
15223 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15224 "' as "sv,
15225 is_arr ? "array-of-tables"sv : "table"sv);
15226 }
15227 }
15228
15229 // need to create a new implicit table
15230 else
15231 {
15232 pit = parent->emplace_hint<table>(pit, make_key(i));
15233 table& p = pit->second.ref_cast<table>();
15234 p.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15235
15236 implicit_tables.push_back(&p);
15237 parent = &p;
15238 }
15239 }
15240
15241 const auto last_segment = key_buffer.back();
15242 auto it = parent->lower_bound(last_segment);
15243
15244 // if there was already a matching node some sanity checking is necessary;
15245 // this is ok if we're making an array and the existing element is already an array (new element)
15246 // or if we're making a table and the existing element is an implicitly-created table (promote it),
15247 // otherwise this is a redefinition error.
15248 if (it != parent->end() && it->first == last_segment)
15249 {
15250 node& matching_node = it->second;
15251 if (auto arr = matching_node.as_array();
15252 is_arr && arr && impl::find(table_arrays.begin(), table_arrays.end(), arr))
15253 {
15254 table& tbl = arr->emplace_back<table>();
15255 tbl.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15256 return &tbl;
15257 }
15258
15259 else if (auto tbl = matching_node.as_table(); !is_arr && tbl && !implicit_tables.empty())
15260 {
15261 if (auto found = impl::find(implicit_tables.begin(), implicit_tables.end(), tbl); found)
15262 {
15263 bool ok = true;
15264 if (!tbl->empty())
15265 {
15266 for (auto& [_, child] : *tbl)
15267 {
15268 if (!child.is_table() && !child.is_array_of_tables())
15269 {
15270 ok = false;
15271 break;
15272 }
15273 }
15274 }
15275
15276 if (ok)
15277 {
15278 implicit_tables.erase(implicit_tables.cbegin() + (found - implicit_tables.data()));
15279 tbl->source_.begin = header_begin_pos;
15280 tbl->source_.end = header_end_pos;
15281 return tbl;
15282 }
15283 }
15284 }
15285
15286 // if we get here it's a redefinition error.
15287 if (!is_arr && matching_node.type() == node_type::table)
15288 {
15289 set_error_at(header_begin_pos,
15290 "cannot redefine existing table '"sv,
15291 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15292 "'"sv);
15293 return_after_error({});
15294 }
15295 else
15296 {
15297 set_error_at(header_begin_pos,
15298 "cannot redefine existing "sv,
15299 to_sv(matching_node.type()),
15300 " '"sv,
15301 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15302 "' as "sv,
15303 is_arr ? "array-of-tables"sv : "table"sv);
15304 return_after_error({});
15305 }
15306 }
15307
15308 // there was no matching node, sweet - we can freely instantiate a new table/table array.
15309 else
15310 {
15311 auto last_key = make_key(key_buffer.size() - 1u);
15312
15313 // if it's an array we need to make the array and it's first table element,
15314 // set the starting regions, and return the table element
15315 if (is_arr)
15316 {
15317 it = parent->emplace_hint<array>(it, std::move(last_key));
15318 array& tbl_arr = it->second.ref_cast<array>();
15319 table_arrays.push_back(&tbl_arr);
15320 tbl_arr.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15321
15322 table& tbl = tbl_arr.emplace_back<table>();
15323 tbl.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15324 return &tbl;
15325 }
15326
15327 // otherwise we're just making a table
15328 else
15329 {
15330 it = parent->emplace_hint<table>(it, std::move(last_key));
15331 table& tbl = it->second.ref_cast<table>();
15332 tbl.source_ = { header_begin_pos, header_end_pos, reader.source_path() };
15333 return &tbl;
15334 }
15335 }
15336 }
15337
15338 TOML_NEVER_INLINE
15339 bool parse_key_value_pair_and_insert(table* tbl)
15340 {
15341 return_if_error({});
15342 assert_not_eof();
15343 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(is_string_delimiter(*cp) || is_bare_key_character(*cp));
15344 push_parse_scope("key-value pair"sv);
15345
15346 // read the key into the key buffer
15347 start_recording();
15348 parse_key();
15349 stop_recording(1u);
15350 return_if_error({});
15351 TOML_ASSERT(key_buffer.size() >= 1u);
15352
15353 // skip past any whitespace that followed the key
15354 consume_leading_whitespace();
15355 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15356
15357 // '='
15358 if (*cp != U'=')
15359 set_error_and_return_default("expected '=', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15360 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15361
15362 // skip past any whitespace that followed the '='
15363 consume_leading_whitespace();
15364 return_if_error({});
15365 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15366
15367 // check that the next character could actually be a value
15368 if (is_value_terminator(*cp))
15369 set_error_and_return_default("expected value, saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15370
15371 // if it's a dotted kvp we need to spawn the parent sub-tables if necessary,
15372 // and set the target table to the second-to-last one in the chain
15373 if (key_buffer.size() > 1u)
15374 {
15375 for (size_t i = 0; i < key_buffer.size() - 1u; i++)
15376 {
15377 const std::string_view segment = key_buffer[i];
15378 auto pit = tbl->lower_bound(segment);
15379
15380 // parent already existed
15381 if (pit != tbl->end() && pit->first == segment)
15382 {
15383 table* p = pit->second.as_table();
15384
15385 // redefinition
15386 if TOML_UNLIKELY(!p
15387 || !(impl::find(dotted_key_tables.begin(), dotted_key_tables.end(), p)
15388 || impl::find(implicit_tables.begin(), implicit_tables.end(), p)))
15389 {
15390 set_error_at(key_buffer.starts[i],
15391 "cannot redefine existing "sv,
15392 to_sv(pit->second.type()),
15393 " as dotted key-value pair"sv);
15394 return_after_error({});
15395 }
15396
15397 tbl = p;
15398 }
15399
15400 // need to create a new implicit table
15401 else
15402 {
15403 pit = tbl->emplace_hint<table>(pit, make_key(i));
15404 table& p = pit->second.ref_cast<table>();
15405 p.source_ = pit->first.source();
15406
15407 dotted_key_tables.push_back(&p);
15408 tbl = &p;
15409 }
15410 }
15411 }
15412
15413 // ensure this isn't a redefinition
15414 const std::string_view last_segment = key_buffer.back();
15415 auto it = tbl->lower_bound(last_segment);
15416 if (it != tbl->end() && it->first == last_segment)
15417 {
15418 set_error("cannot redefine existing "sv,
15419 to_sv(it->second.type()),
15420 " '"sv,
15421 to_sv(recording_buffer),
15422 "'"sv);
15423 return_after_error({});
15424 }
15425
15426 // create the key first since the key buffer will likely get overwritten during value parsing (inline
15427 // tables)
15428 auto last_key = make_key(key_buffer.size() - 1u);
15429
15430 // now we can actually parse the value
15431 node_ptr val = parse_value();
15432 return_if_error({});
15433
15434 tbl->emplace_hint<node_ptr>(it, std::move(last_key), std::move(val));
15435 return true;
15436 }
15437
15438 void parse_document()
15439 {
15440 assert_not_error();
15441 assert_not_eof();
15442 push_parse_scope("root table"sv);
15443
15444 table* current_table = &root;
15445
15446 do
15447 {
15448 return_if_error();
15449
15450 // leading whitespace, line endings, comments
15451 if (consume_leading_whitespace() || consume_line_break() || consume_comment())
15452 continue;
15453 return_if_error();
15454
15455 // [tables]
15456 // [[table array]]
15457 if (*cp == U'[')
15458 current_table = parse_table_header();
15459
15460 // bare_keys
15461 // dotted.keys
15462 // "quoted keys"
15463 else if (is_bare_key_character(*cp) || is_string_delimiter(*cp))
15464 {
15465 push_parse_scope("key-value pair"sv);
15466
15467 parse_key_value_pair_and_insert(current_table);
15468
15469 // handle the rest of the line after the kvp
15470 // (this is not done in parse_key_value_pair() because that is also used for inline tables)
15471 consume_leading_whitespace();
15472 return_if_error();
15473 if (!is_eof() && !consume_comment() && !consume_line_break())
15474 set_error("expected a comment or whitespace, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
15475 }
15476
15477 else // ??
15478 set_error("expected keys, tables, whitespace or comments, saw '"sv, to_sv(cp), "'"sv);
15479 }
15480 while (!is_eof());
15481
15482 auto eof_pos = current_position(1);
15483 root.source_.end = eof_pos;
15484 if (current_table && current_table != &root && current_table->source_.end <= current_table->source_.begin)
15485 current_table->source_.end = eof_pos;
15486 }
15487
15488 static void update_region_ends(node& nde) noexcept
15489 {
15490 const auto type = nde.type();
15491 if (type > node_type::array)
15492 return;
15493
15494 if (type == node_type::table)
15495 {
15496 auto& tbl = nde.ref_cast<table>();
15497 if (tbl.is_inline()) // inline tables (and all their inline descendants) are already correctly
15498 // terminated
15499 return;
15500
15501 auto end = nde.source_.end;
15502 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
15503 {
15504 TOML_UNUSED(k);
15505 update_region_ends(v);
15506 if (end < v.source_.end)
15507 end = v.source_.end;
15508 }
15509 }
15510 else // arrays
15511 {
15512 auto& arr = nde.ref_cast<array>();
15513 auto end = nde.source_.end;
15514 for (auto&& v : arr)
15515 {
15516 update_region_ends(v);
15517 if (end < v.source_.end)
15518 end = v.source_.end;
15519 }
15520 nde.source_.end = end;
15521 }
15522 }
15523
15524 public:
15525 parser(utf8_reader_interface&& reader_) //
15526 : reader{ reader_ }
15527 {
15528 root.source_ = { prev_pos, prev_pos, reader.source_path() };
15529
15530 if (!reader.peek_eof())
15531 {
15532 cp = reader.read_next();
15533
15534#if !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15535 if (reader.error())
15536 {
15537 err = std::move(reader.error());
15538 return;
15539 }
15540#endif
15541
15542 if (cp)
15543 parse_document();
15544 }
15545
15546 update_region_ends(root);
15547 }
15548
15549 TOML_NODISCARD
15550 operator parse_result() && noexcept
15551 {
15552#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15553
15554 return { std::move(root) };
15555
15556#else
15557
15558 if (err)
15559 return parse_result{ *std::move(err) };
15560 else
15561 return parse_result{ std::move(root) };
15562
15563#endif
15564 }
15565 };
15566
15567 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
15568 node_ptr parser::parse_array()
15569 {
15570 return_if_error({});
15571 assert_not_eof();
15572 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'[');
15573 push_parse_scope("array"sv);
15574
15575 // skip opening '['
15576 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15577
15578 node_ptr arr_ptr{ new array{} };
15579 array& arr = arr_ptr->ref_cast<array>();
15580 enum class TOML_CLOSED_ENUM parse_type : int
15581 {
15582 none,
15583 comma,
15584 val
15585 };
15586 parse_type prev = parse_type::none;
15587
15588 while (!is_error())
15589 {
15590 while (consume_leading_whitespace() || consume_line_break() || consume_comment())
15591 continue;
15592 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15593
15594 // commas - only legal after a value
15595 if (*cp == U',')
15596 {
15597 if (prev == parse_type::val)
15598 {
15599 prev = parse_type::comma;
15600 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15601 continue;
15602 }
15603 set_error_and_return_default("expected value or closing ']', saw comma"sv);
15604 }
15605
15606 // closing ']'
15607 else if (*cp == U']')
15608 {
15609 advance_and_return_if_error({});
15610 break;
15611 }
15612
15613 // must be a value
15614 else
15615 {
15616 if (prev == parse_type::val)
15617 {
15618 set_error_and_return_default("expected comma or closing ']', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15619 continue;
15620 }
15621 prev = parse_type::val;
15622
15623 auto val = parse_value();
15624 return_if_error({});
15625
15626 if (!arr.capacity())
15627 arr.reserve(4u);
15628 arr.emplace_back<node_ptr>(std::move(val));
15629 }
15630 }
15631
15632 return_if_error({});
15633 return arr_ptr;
15634 }
15635
15636 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
15637 node_ptr parser::parse_inline_table()
15638 {
15639 return_if_error({});
15640 assert_not_eof();
15641 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(*cp == U'{');
15642 push_parse_scope("inline table"sv);
15643
15644 // skip opening '{'
15645 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15646
15647 node_ptr tbl_ptr{ new table{} };
15648 table& tbl = tbl_ptr->ref_cast<table>();
15649 tbl.is_inline(true);
15650 table_vector_scope table_scope{ open_inline_tables, tbl };
15651
15652 enum class TOML_CLOSED_ENUM parse_type : int
15653 {
15654 none,
15655 comma,
15656 kvp
15657 };
15658 parse_type prev = parse_type::none;
15659 while (!is_error())
15660 {
15661 if constexpr (TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED) // toml/issues/516 (newlines/trailing commas in inline tables)
15662 {
15663 while (consume_leading_whitespace() || consume_line_break() || consume_comment())
15664 continue;
15665 }
15666 else
15667 {
15668 while (consume_leading_whitespace())
15669 continue;
15670 }
15671 return_if_error({});
15672 set_error_and_return_if_eof({});
15673
15674 // commas - only legal after a key-value pair
15675 if (*cp == U',')
15676 {
15677 if (prev == parse_type::kvp)
15678 {
15679 prev = parse_type::comma;
15680 advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof({});
15681 }
15682 else
15683 set_error_and_return_default("expected key-value pair or closing '}', saw comma"sv);
15684 }
15685
15686 // closing '}'
15687 else if (*cp == U'}')
15688 {
15689 if constexpr (!TOML_LANG_UNRELEASED) // toml/issues/516 (newlines/trailing commas in inline tables)
15690 {
15691 if (prev == parse_type::comma)
15692 {
15693 set_error_and_return_default("expected key-value pair, saw closing '}' (dangling comma)"sv);
15694 continue;
15695 }
15696 }
15697 advance_and_return_if_error({});
15698 break;
15699 }
15700
15701 // key-value pair
15702 else if (is_string_delimiter(*cp) || is_bare_key_character(*cp))
15703 {
15704 if (prev == parse_type::kvp)
15705 set_error_and_return_default("expected comma or closing '}', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15706 else
15707 {
15708 prev = parse_type::kvp;
15709 parse_key_value_pair_and_insert(&tbl);
15710 }
15711 }
15712
15713 else
15714 set_error_and_return_default("expected key or closing '}', saw '"sv, to_sv(*cp), "'"sv);
15715 }
15716
15717 return_if_error({});
15718 return tbl_ptr;
15719 }
15720
15721 TOML_ABI_NAMESPACE_END; // TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15722}
15723TOML_IMPL_NAMESPACE_END;
15724
15725#undef TOML_RETURNS_BY_THROWING
15726#undef advance_and_return_if_error
15727#undef advance_and_return_if_error_or_eof
15728#undef assert_not_eof
15729#undef assert_not_error
15730#undef is_eof
15731#undef is_error
15732#undef parse_error_break
15733#undef push_parse_scope
15734#undef push_parse_scope_1
15735#undef push_parse_scope_2
15736#undef return_after_error
15737#undef return_if_eof
15738#undef return_if_error
15739#undef return_if_error_or_eof
15740#undef set_error_and_return
15741#undef set_error_and_return_default
15742#undef set_error_and_return_if_eof
15743#undef utf8_buffered_reader_error_check
15744#undef utf8_reader_error
15745#undef utf8_reader_error_check
15746#undef utf8_reader_return_after_error

15749{
15750 TOML_NODISCARD
15751 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
15752 parse_result do_parse(utf8_reader_interface && reader)
15753 {
15754 return impl::parser{ std::move(reader) };
15755 }
15756
15757 TOML_NODISCARD
15758 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
15759 parse_result do_parse_file(std::string_view file_path)
15760 {
15761#if TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15762#define TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR(msg, path) \
15763 throw parse_error{ msg, source_position{}, std::make_shared<const std::string>(std::move(path)) }
15764#else
15765#define TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR(msg, path) \
15766 return parse_result \
15767 { \
15768 parse_error \
15769 { \
15770 msg, source_position{}, std::make_shared<const std::string>(std::move(path)) \
15771 } \
15772 }
15773#endif
15774
15775 std::string file_path_str(file_path);
15776
15777 // open file with a custom-sized stack buffer
15778 std::ifstream file;
15779 TOML_OVERALIGNED char file_buffer[sizeof(void*) * 1024u];
15780 file.rdbuf()->pubsetbuf(file_buffer, sizeof(file_buffer));
15781#if TOML_WINDOWS
15782 file.open(impl::widen(file_path_str).c_str(), std::ifstream::in | std::ifstream::binary | std::ifstream::ate);
15783#else
15784 file.open(file_path_str, std::ifstream::in | std::ifstream::binary | std::ifstream::ate);
15785#endif
15786 if (!file.is_open())
15787 TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR("File could not be opened for reading", file_path_str);
15788
15789 // get size
15790 const auto file_size = file.tellg();
15791 if (file_size == -1)
15792 TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR("Could not determine file size", file_path_str);
15793 file.seekg(0, std::ifstream::beg);
15794
15795 // read the whole file into memory first if the file isn't too large
15796 constexpr auto large_file_threshold = 1024 * 1024 * 2; // 2 MB
15797 if (file_size <= large_file_threshold)
15798 {
15799 std::vector<char> file_data;
15800 file_data.resize(static_cast<size_t>(file_size));
15801 file.read(file_data.data(), static_cast<std::streamsize>(file_size));
15802 return parse(std::string_view{ file_data.data(), file_data.size() }, std::move(file_path_str));
15803 }
15804
15805 // otherwise parse it using the streams
15806 else
15807 return parse(file, std::move(file_path_str));
15808
15809#undef TOML_PARSE_FILE_ERROR
15810 }
15811}
15812TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE_END;
15813
15814TOML_NAMESPACE_START

15816 TOML_ABI_NAMESPACE_BOOL(TOML_EXCEPTIONS, ex, noex);

15822 }

15934{
15935 enum class TOML_CLOSED_FLAGS_ENUM formatted_string_traits : unsigned
15936 {
15937 none,
15938 line_breaks = 1u << 0, // \n
15939 tabs = 1u << 1, // \t
15940 control_chars = 1u << 2, // also includes non-ascii vertical whitespace
15941 single_quotes = 1u << 3,
15942 non_bare = 1u << 4, // anything not satisfying "is bare key character"
15943 non_ascii = 1u << 5, // any codepoint >= 128
15944
15945 all = (non_ascii << 1u) - 1u
15946 };
15947 TOML_MAKE_FLAGS(formatted_string_traits);
15948
15949 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
15950 formatter::formatter(const node* source_node,
15951 const parse_result* source_pr,
15952 const formatter_constants& constants,
15953 const formatter_config& config) noexcept //
15954#if TOML_ENABLE_PARSER && !TOML_EXCEPTIONS
15955 : source_{ source_pr && *source_pr ? &source_pr->table() : source_node },
15956 result_{ source_pr },
15957#else
15958 : source_{ source_pr ? source_pr : source_node },
15959#endif
15960 constants_{ &constants },
15961 config_{ config }
15962 {
15963 TOML_ASSERT_ASSUME(source_);
15964
15965 config_.flags = (config_.flags | constants_->mandatory_flags) & ~constants_->ignored_flags;
15966
15967 indent_columns_ = {};
15968 for (auto c : config_.indent)
15969 indent_columns_ += c == '\t' ? 4u : 1u;
15970
15971 int_format_mask_ = config_.flags
15972 & (format_flags::allow_binary_integers | format_flags::allow_octal_integers
15973 | format_flags::allow_hexadecimal_integers);
15974 }
15975

15977 void formatter::attach(std::ostream & stream) noexcept
15978 {
15979 indent_ = {};
15980 naked_newline_ = true;
15981 stream_ = &stream;
15982 }
15983
15984 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
15985 void formatter::detach() noexcept
15986 {
15987 stream_ = nullptr;
15988 }

16017 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE

16023
16024 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16025 void formatter::print_string(std::string_view str, bool allow_multi_line, bool allow_bare)
16026 {
16027 if (str.empty())
16028 {
16029 print_unformatted(literal_strings_allowed() ? "''"sv : "\"\""sv);
16030 return;
16031 }
16032
16033 // pre-scan the string to determine how we should output it
16034 formatted_string_traits traits = {};
16035
16036 if (!allow_bare)
16037 traits |= formatted_string_traits::non_bare;
16038 bool unicode_allowed = unicode_strings_allowed();
16039
16040 // ascii fast path
16041 if (is_ascii(str.data(), str.length()))
16042 {
16043 for (auto c : str)
16044 {
16045 switch (c)
16046 {
16047 case '\n': traits |= formatted_string_traits::line_breaks; break;
16048 case '\t': traits |= formatted_string_traits::tabs; break;
16049 case '\'': traits |= formatted_string_traits::single_quotes; break;
16050 default:
16051 {
16052 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_control_character(c))
16053 traits |= formatted_string_traits::control_chars;
16054
16055 if (!is_ascii_bare_key_character(static_cast<char32_t>(c)))
16056 traits |= formatted_string_traits::non_bare;
16057 break;
16058 }
16059 }
16060
16061 static constexpr auto all_ascii_traits =
16062 formatted_string_traits::all & ~formatted_string_traits::non_ascii;
16063 if (traits == all_ascii_traits)
16064 break;
16065 }
16066 }
16067
16068 // unicode slow path
16069 else
16070 {
16071 traits |= formatted_string_traits::non_ascii;
16072 utf8_decoder decoder;
16073
16074 // if the unicode is malformed just treat the string as a single-line non-literal and
16075 // escape all non-ascii characters (to ensure round-tripping and help with diagnostics)
16076 const auto bad_unicode = [&]() noexcept
16077 {
16078 traits &= ~formatted_string_traits::line_breaks;
16079 traits |= formatted_string_traits::control_chars | formatted_string_traits::non_bare;
16080 unicode_allowed = false;
16081 };
16082
16083 for (auto c : str)
16084 {
16085 decoder(c);
16086
16087 if TOML_UNLIKELY(decoder.error())
16088 {
16089 bad_unicode();
16090 break;
16091 }
16092
16093 if (!decoder.has_code_point())
16094 continue;
16095
16096 switch (decoder.codepoint)
16097 {
16098 case U'\n': traits |= formatted_string_traits::line_breaks; break;
16099 case U'\t': traits |= formatted_string_traits::tabs; break;
16100 case U'\'': traits |= formatted_string_traits::single_quotes; break;
16101 default:
16102 {
16103 if TOML_UNLIKELY(is_control_character(decoder.codepoint)
16104 || is_non_ascii_vertical_whitespace(decoder.codepoint))
16105 traits |= formatted_string_traits::control_chars;
16106
16107 if (!is_bare_key_character(decoder.codepoint))
16108 traits |= formatted_string_traits::non_bare;
16109 break;
16110 }
16111 }
16112 }
16113
16114 if (decoder.needs_more_input())
16115 bad_unicode();
16116 }
16117
16118 // if the string meets the requirements of being 'bare' we can emit a bare string
16119 // (bare strings are composed of letters and numbers; no whitespace, control chars, quotes, etc)
16120 if (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::non_bare)
16121 && (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::non_ascii) || unicode_allowed))
16122 {
16123 print_unformatted(str);
16124 return;
16125 }
16126
16127 // determine if this should be a multi-line string (triple-quotes)
16128 const auto multi_line = allow_multi_line //
16129 && multi_line_strings_allowed() //
16130 && !!(traits & formatted_string_traits::line_breaks);
16131
16132 // determine if this should be a literal string (single-quotes with no escaping)
16133 const auto literal = literal_strings_allowed() //
16134 && !(traits & formatted_string_traits::control_chars) //
16135 && (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::single_quotes) || multi_line) //
16136 && (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::tabs) || real_tabs_in_strings_allowed()) //
16137 && (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::non_ascii) || unicode_allowed);
16138
16139 // literal strings (single quotes, no escape codes)
16140 if (literal)
16141 {
16142 const auto quot = multi_line ? R"(''')"sv : R"(')"sv;
16143 print_unformatted(quot);
16144 print_unformatted(str);
16145 print_unformatted(quot);
16146 return;
16147 }
16148
16149 // anything from here down is a non-literal string, so requires iteration and escaping.
16150 print_unformatted(multi_line ? R"(""")"sv : R"(")"sv);
16151
16152 const auto real_tabs_allowed = real_tabs_in_strings_allowed();
16153
16154 // ascii fast path
16155 if (!(traits & formatted_string_traits::non_ascii))
16156 {
16157 for (auto c : str)
16158 {
16159 switch (c)
16160 {
16161 case '"': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\")"sv); break;
16162 case '\\': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\\)"sv); break;
16163 case '\x7F': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\u007F)"sv); break;
16164 case '\t': print_to_stream(*stream_, real_tabs_allowed ? "\t"sv : R"(\t)"sv); break;
16165 case '\n': print_to_stream(*stream_, multi_line ? "\n"sv : R"(\n)"sv); break;
16166 default:
16167 {
16168 // control characters from lookup table
16169 if TOML_UNLIKELY(c >= '\x00' && c <= '\x1F')
16170 print_to_stream(*stream_, control_char_escapes[c]);
16171
16172 // regular characters
16173 else
16174 print_to_stream(*stream_, c);
16175 }
16176 }
16177 }
16178 }
16179
16180 // unicode slow path
16181 else
16182 {
16183 utf8_decoder decoder;
16184 const char* cp_start = str.data();
16185 const char* cp_end = cp_start;
16186 for (auto c : str)
16187 {
16188 decoder(c);
16189 cp_end++;
16190
16191 // if the decoder encounters malformed unicode just emit raw bytes and
16192 if (decoder.error())
16193 {
16194 while (cp_start != cp_end)
16195 {
16196 print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\u00)"sv);
16197 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16198 static_cast<uint8_t>(*cp_start),
16199 value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal,
16200 2);
16201 cp_start++;
16202 }
16203 decoder.reset();
16204 continue;
16205 }
16206
16207 if (!decoder.has_code_point())
16208 continue;
16209
16210 switch (decoder.codepoint)
16211 {
16212 case U'"': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\")"sv); break;
16213 case U'\\': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\\)"sv); break;
16214 case U'\x7F': print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\u007F)"sv); break;
16215 case U'\t': print_to_stream(*stream_, real_tabs_allowed ? "\t"sv : R"(\t)"sv); break;
16216 case U'\n': print_to_stream(*stream_, multi_line ? "\n"sv : R"(\n)"sv); break;
16217 default:
16218 {
16219 // control characters from lookup table
16220 if TOML_UNLIKELY(decoder.codepoint <= U'\x1F')
16221 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16222 control_char_escapes[static_cast<uint_least32_t>(decoder.codepoint)]);
16223
16224 // escaped unicode characters
16225 else if (decoder.codepoint > U'\x7F'
16226 && (!unicode_allowed || is_non_ascii_vertical_whitespace(decoder.codepoint)))
16227 {
16228 if (static_cast<uint_least32_t>(decoder.codepoint) > 0xFFFFu)
16229 {
16230 print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\U)"sv);
16231 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16232 static_cast<uint_least32_t>(decoder.codepoint),
16233 value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal,
16234 8);
16235 }
16236 else
16237 {
16238 print_to_stream(*stream_, R"(\u)"sv);
16239 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16240 static_cast<uint_least32_t>(decoder.codepoint),
16241 value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal,
16242 4);
16243 }
16244 }
16245
16246 // regular characters
16247 else
16248 print_to_stream(*stream_, cp_start, static_cast<size_t>(cp_end - cp_start));
16249 }
16250 }
16251
16252 cp_start = cp_end;
16253 }
16254 }
16255
16256 print_unformatted(multi_line ? R"(""")"sv : R"(")"sv);
16257 }
16258
16259 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16260 void formatter::print(const value<std::string>& val)
16261 {
16262 print_string(val.get());
16263 }
16264
16265 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16266 void formatter::print(const value<int64_t>& val)
16267 {
16268 naked_newline_ = false;
16269
16270 if (*val >= 0 && !!int_format_mask_)
16271 {
16272 static constexpr auto value_flags_mask =
16273 value_flags::format_as_binary | value_flags::format_as_octal | value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal;
16274
16275 const auto fmt = val.flags() & value_flags_mask;
16276 switch (fmt)
16277 {
16278 case value_flags::format_as_binary:
16279 if (!!(int_format_mask_ & format_flags::allow_binary_integers))
16280 {
16281 print_to_stream(*stream_, "0b"sv);
16282 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val, fmt);
16283 return;
16284 }
16285 break;
16286
16287 case value_flags::format_as_octal:
16288 if (!!(int_format_mask_ & format_flags::allow_octal_integers))
16289 {
16290 print_to_stream(*stream_, "0o"sv);
16291 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val, fmt);
16292 return;
16293 }
16294 break;
16295
16296 case value_flags::format_as_hexadecimal:
16297 if (!!(int_format_mask_ & format_flags::allow_hexadecimal_integers))
16298 {
16299 print_to_stream(*stream_, "0x"sv);
16300 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val, fmt);
16301 return;
16302 }
16303 break;
16304
16305 default: break;
16306 }
16307 }
16308
16309 // fallback to decimal
16310 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val);
16311 }
16312
16313 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16314 void formatter::print(const value<double>& val)
16315 {
16316 const std::string_view* inf_nan = nullptr;
16317 switch (fpclassify(*val))
16318 {
16319 case fp_class::neg_inf: inf_nan = &constants_->float_neg_inf; break;
16320 case fp_class::pos_inf: inf_nan = &constants_->float_pos_inf; break;
16321 case fp_class::nan: inf_nan = &constants_->float_nan; break;
16322 case fp_class::ok:
16323 print_to_stream(*stream_,
16324 *val,
16325 value_flags::none,
16326 !!(config_.flags & format_flags::relaxed_float_precision));
16327 break;
16328 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16329 }
16330
16331 if (inf_nan)
16332 {
16333 if (!!(config_.flags & format_flags::quote_infinities_and_nans))
16334 print_to_stream_bookended(*stream_, *inf_nan, '"');
16335 else
16336 print_to_stream(*stream_, *inf_nan);
16337 }
16338
16339 naked_newline_ = false;
16340 }
16341
16342 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16343 void formatter::print(const value<bool>& val)
16344 {
16345 print_unformatted(*val ? constants_->bool_true : constants_->bool_false);
16346 }
16347

16349 void formatter::print(const value<date>& val)
16350 {
16351 if (!!(config_.flags & format_flags::quote_dates_and_times))
16352 print_to_stream_bookended(*stream_, *val, literal_strings_allowed() ? '\'' : '"');
16353 else
16354 print_to_stream(*stream_, *val);
16355 naked_newline_ = false;
16356 }

16363 else

16378 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16379 void formatter::print_value(const node& val_node, node_type type)
16380 {
16381 TOML_ASSUME(type > node_type::array);
16382 switch (type)
16383 {
16384 case node_type::string: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&val_node)); break;
16385 case node_type::integer: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<int64_t>*>(&val_node)); break;
16386 case node_type::floating_point: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<double>*>(&val_node)); break;
16387 case node_type::boolean: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<bool>*>(&val_node)); break;
16388 case node_type::date: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<date>*>(&val_node)); break;
16389 case node_type::time: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<time>*>(&val_node)); break;
16390 case node_type::date_time: print(*reinterpret_cast<const value<date_time>*>(&val_node)); break;
16391 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16392 }
16393 }

16438#pragma push_macro("max")

16445TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE_START
16446{
16447 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
16448 size_t toml_formatter_count_inline_columns(const node& node, size_t line_wrap_cols) noexcept
16449 {
16450 switch (node.type())
16451 {
16452 case node_type::table:
16453 {
16454 auto& tbl = *reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&node);
16455 if (tbl.empty())
16456 return 2u; // "{}"
16457 size_t weight = 3u; // "{ }"
16458 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16459 {
16460 weight += k.length() + toml_formatter_count_inline_columns(v, line_wrap_cols) + 2u; // + ", "
16461 if (weight >= line_wrap_cols)
16462 break;
16463 }
16464 return weight;
16465 }
16466
16467 case node_type::array:
16468 {
16469 auto& arr = *reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&node);
16470 if (arr.empty())
16471 return 2u; // "[]"
16472 size_t weight = 3u; // "[ ]"
16473 for (auto& elem : arr)
16474 {
16475 weight += toml_formatter_count_inline_columns(elem, line_wrap_cols) + 2u; // + ", "
16476 if (weight >= line_wrap_cols)
16477 break;
16478 }
16479 return weight;
16480 }
16481
16482 case node_type::string:
16483 {
16484 // todo: proper utf8 decoding?
16485 // todo: tab awareness?
16486 auto& str = (*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&node)).get();
16487 return str.length() + 2u; // + ""
16488 }
16489
16490 case node_type::integer:
16491 {
16492 auto val = (*reinterpret_cast<const value<int64_t>*>(&node)).get();
16493 if (!val)
16494 return 1u;
16495 size_t weight = {};
16496 if (val < 0)
16497 {
16498 weight += 1u;
16499 val *= -1;
16500 }
16501 return weight + static_cast<size_t>(log10(static_cast<double>(val))) + 1u;
16502 }
16503
16504 case node_type::floating_point:
16505 {
16506 auto val = (*reinterpret_cast<const value<double>*>(&node)).get();
16507 if (val == 0.0)
16508 return 3u; // "0.0"
16509 size_t weight = 2u; // ".0"
16510 if (val < 0.0)
16511 {
16512 weight += 1u;
16513 val *= -1.0;
16514 }
16515 return weight + static_cast<size_t>(log10(val)) + 1u;
16516 break;
16517 }
16518
16519 case node_type::boolean: return 5u;
16520 case node_type::date: [[fallthrough]];
16521 case node_type::time: return 10u;
16522 case node_type::date_time: return 30u;
16523 case node_type::none: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16524 default: TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16525 }
16526
16527 TOML_UNREACHABLE;
16528 }
16529
16530 TOML_INTERNAL_LINKAGE
16531 bool toml_formatter_forces_multiline(const node& node, size_t line_wrap_cols, size_t starting_column_bias) noexcept
16532 {
16533 return (toml_formatter_count_inline_columns(node, line_wrap_cols) + starting_column_bias) >= line_wrap_cols;
16534 }
16535}
16536TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE_END;

16539{
16540 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16541 void toml_formatter::print_pending_table_separator()
16542 {
16543 if (pending_table_separator_)
16544 {
16545 print_newline(true);
16546 print_newline(true);
16547 pending_table_separator_ = false;
16548 }
16549 }

16552 void toml_formatter::print(const key& k)

16554 print_string(k.str(), false, true);

16556
16557 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16558 void toml_formatter::print_inline(const table& tbl)
16559 {
16560 if (tbl.empty())
16561 {
16562 print_unformatted("{}"sv);
16563 return;
16564 }
16565
16566 print_unformatted("{ "sv);
16567
16568 bool first = false;
16569 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16570 {
16571 if (first)
16572 print_unformatted(", "sv);
16573 first = true;
16574
16575 print(k);
16576 if (terse_kvps())
16577 print_unformatted("="sv);
16578 else
16579 print_unformatted(" = "sv);
16580
16581 const auto type = v.type();
16582 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16583 switch (type)
16584 {
16585 case node_type::table: print_inline(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16586 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16587 default: print_value(v, type);
16588 }
16589 }
16590
16591 print_unformatted(" }"sv);
16592 }
16593
16594 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16595 void toml_formatter::print(const array& arr)
16596 {
16597 if (arr.empty())
16598 {
16599 print_unformatted("[]"sv);
16600 return;
16601 }
16602
16603 const auto original_indent = indent();
16604 const auto multiline = TOML_ANON_NAMESPACE::toml_formatter_forces_multiline(
16605 arr,
16606 120u,
16607 indent_columns() * static_cast<size_t>(original_indent < 0 ? 0 : original_indent));
16608
16609 print_unformatted("["sv);
16610
16611 if (multiline)
16612 {
16613 if (original_indent < 0)
16614 indent(0);
16615 if (indent_array_elements())
16616 increase_indent();
16617 }
16618 else
16619 print_unformatted(' ');
16620
16621 for (size_t i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++)
16622 {
16623 if (i > 0u)
16624 {
16625 print_unformatted(',');
16626 if (!multiline)
16627 print_unformatted(' ');
16628 }
16629
16630 if (multiline)
16631 {
16632 print_newline(true);
16633 print_indent();
16634 }
16635
16636 auto& v = arr[i];
16637 const auto type = v.type();
16638 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16639 switch (type)
16640 {
16641 case node_type::table: print_inline(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16642 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16643 default: print_value(v, type);
16644 }
16645 }
16646 if (multiline)
16647 {
16648 indent(original_indent);
16649 print_newline(true);
16650 print_indent();
16651 }
16652 else
16653 print_unformatted(' ');
16654
16655 print_unformatted("]"sv);
16656 }
16657
16658 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16659 void toml_formatter::print(const table& tbl)
16660 {
16661 static constexpr auto is_non_inline_array_of_tables = [](const node& n) noexcept
16662 {
16663 const auto arr = n.as_array();
16664 if (!arr || !arr->is_array_of_tables())
16665 return false;
16666
16667 return !reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&(*arr)[0])->is_inline();
16668 };
16669
16670 // values, arrays, and inline tables/table arrays
16671 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16672 {
16673 const auto type = v.type();
16674 if ((type == node_type::table && !reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)->is_inline())
16675 || (type == node_type::array && is_non_inline_array_of_tables(v)))
16676 continue;
16677
16678 pending_table_separator_ = true;
16679 print_newline();
16680 print_indent();
16681 print(k);
16682 if (terse_kvps())
16683 print_unformatted("="sv);
16684 else
16685 print_unformatted(" = "sv);
16686 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16687 switch (type)
16688 {
16689 case node_type::table: print_inline(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16690 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16691 default: print_value(v, type);
16692 }
16693 }
16694
16695 const auto print_key_path = [&]()
16696 {
16697 size_t i{};
16698 for (const auto k : key_path_)
16699 {
16700 if (i++)
16701 print_unformatted('.');
16702 print(*k);
16703 }
16704 };
16705
16706 // non-inline tables
16707 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16708 {
16709 const auto type = v.type();
16710 if (type != node_type::table || reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)->is_inline())
16711 continue;
16712 auto& child_tbl = *reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v);
16713
16714 // we can skip indenting and emitting the headers for tables that only contain other tables
16715 // (so we don't over-nest)
16716 size_t child_value_count{}; // includes inline tables and non-table arrays
16717 size_t child_table_count{};
16718 size_t child_table_array_count{};
16719 for (auto&& [child_k, child_v] : child_tbl)
16720 {
16721 TOML_UNUSED(child_k);
16722 const auto child_type = child_v.type();
16723 TOML_ASSUME(child_type != node_type::none);
16724 switch (child_type)
16725 {
16726 case node_type::table:
16727 if (reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&child_v)->is_inline())
16728 child_value_count++;
16729 else
16730 child_table_count++;
16731 break;
16732
16733 case node_type::array:
16734 if (is_non_inline_array_of_tables(child_v))
16735 child_table_array_count++;
16736 else
16737 child_value_count++;
16738 break;
16739
16740 default: child_value_count++;
16741 }
16742 }
16743 bool skip_self = false;
16744 if (child_value_count == 0u && (child_table_count > 0u || child_table_array_count > 0u))
16745 skip_self = true;
16746
16747 key_path_.push_back(&k);
16748
16749 if (!skip_self)
16750 {
16751 print_pending_table_separator();
16752 if (indent_sub_tables())
16753 increase_indent();
16754 print_indent();
16755 print_unformatted("["sv);
16756 print_key_path();
16757 print_unformatted("]"sv);
16758 pending_table_separator_ = true;
16759 }
16760
16761 print(child_tbl);
16762
16763 key_path_.pop_back();
16764 if (!skip_self && indent_sub_tables())
16765 decrease_indent();
16766 }
16767
16768 // table arrays
16769 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16770 {
16771 if (!is_non_inline_array_of_tables(v))
16772 continue;
16773 auto& arr = *reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v);
16774
16775 if (indent_sub_tables())
16776 increase_indent();
16777 key_path_.push_back(&k);
16778
16779 for (size_t i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++)
16780 {
16781 print_pending_table_separator();
16782 print_indent();
16783 print_unformatted("[["sv);
16784 print_key_path();
16785 print_unformatted("]]"sv);
16786 pending_table_separator_ = true;
16787 print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&arr[i]));
16788 }
16789
16790 key_path_.pop_back();
16791 if (indent_sub_tables())
16792 decrease_indent();
16793 }
16794 }
16795
16796 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16797 void toml_formatter::print()
16798 {
16799 if (dump_failed_parse_result())
16800 return;
16801
16802 switch (auto source_type = source().type())
16803 {
16804 case node_type::table:
16805 {
16806 auto& tbl = *reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&source());
16807 if (tbl.is_inline())
16808 print_inline(tbl);
16809 else
16810 {
16811 decrease_indent(); // so root kvps and tables have the same indent
16812 print(tbl);
16813 }
16814 break;
16815 }
16816
16817 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&source())); break;
16818
16819 default: print_value(source(), source_type);
16820 }
16821 }
16822}

16849 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16850 void json_formatter::print(const toml::table& tbl)
16851 {
16852 if (tbl.empty())
16853 {
16854 print_unformatted("{}"sv);
16855 return;
16856 }
16857
16858 print_unformatted('{');
16859
16860 if (indent_sub_tables())
16861 increase_indent();
16862 bool first = false;
16863 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
16864 {
16865 if (first)
16866 print_unformatted(',');
16867 first = true;
16868 print_newline(true);
16869 print_indent();
16870
16871 print_string(k.str(), false);
16872 if (terse_kvps())
16873 print_unformatted(":"sv);
16874 else
16875 print_unformatted(" : "sv);
16876
16877 const auto type = v.type();
16878 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
16879 switch (type)
16880 {
16881 case node_type::table: print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16882 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16883 default: print_value(v, type);
16884 }
16885 }
16886 if (indent_sub_tables())
16887 decrease_indent();
16888 print_newline(true);
16889 print_indent();
16890
16891 print_unformatted('}');
16892 }

16908 if (i > 0u)
16909 print_unformatted(',');
16910 print_newline(true);

16916 switch (type)
16917 {
16918 case node_type::table: print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
16919 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
16920 default: print_value(v, type);
16921 }
16922 }
16923 if (indent_array_elements())
16924 decrease_indent();
16925 print_newline(true);
16926 print_indent();
16927 print_unformatted(']');
16928 }

16957#if TOML_ENABLE_FORMATTERS
16958
16959TOML_PUSH_WARNINGS;
16960#ifdef _MSC_VER

16969{
16970 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
16971 void yaml_formatter::print_yaml_string(const value<std::string>& str)
16972 {
16973 if (str->empty())
16974 {
16975 base::print(str);
16976 return;
16977 }
16978
16979 bool contains_newline = false;
16980 for (auto c = str->c_str(), e = str->c_str() + str->length(); c < e && !contains_newline; c++)
16981 contains_newline = *c == '\n';
16982
16983 if (contains_newline)
16984 {
16985 print_unformatted("|-"sv);
16986
16987 increase_indent();
16988
16989 auto line_end = str->c_str() - 1u;
16990 const auto end = str->c_str() + str->length();
16991 while (line_end != end)
16992 {
16993 auto line_start = line_end + 1u;
16994 line_end = line_start;
16995 for (; line_end != end && *line_end != '\n'; line_end++)
16996 ;
16997
16998 if TOML_LIKELY(line_start != line_end || line_end != end)
16999 {
17000 print_newline();
17001 print_indent();
17002 print_unformatted(std::string_view{ line_start, static_cast<size_t>(line_end - line_start) });
17003 }
17004 }
17005
17006 decrease_indent();
17007 }
17008 else
17009 print_string(*str, false, true);
17010 }
17011
17012 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
17013 void yaml_formatter::print(const toml::table& tbl, bool parent_is_array)
17014 {
17015 if (tbl.empty())
17016 {
17017 print_unformatted("{}"sv);
17018 return;
17019 }
17020
17021 increase_indent();
17022
17023 for (auto&& [k, v] : tbl)
17024 {
17025 if (!parent_is_array)
17026 {
17027 print_newline();
17028 print_indent();
17029 }
17030 parent_is_array = false;
17031
17032 print_string(k.str(), false, true);
17033 if (terse_kvps())
17034 print_unformatted(":"sv);
17035 else
17036 print_unformatted(": "sv);
17037
17038 const auto type = v.type();
17039 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
17040 switch (type)
17041 {
17042 case node_type::table: print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v)); break;
17043 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v)); break;
17044 case node_type::string: print_yaml_string(*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&v)); break;
17045 default: print_value(v, type);
17046 }
17047 }
17048
17049 decrease_indent();
17050 }
17051
17052 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
17053 void yaml_formatter::print(const toml::array& arr, bool parent_is_array)
17054 {
17055 if (arr.empty())
17056 {
17057 print_unformatted("[]"sv);
17058 return;
17059 }
17060
17061 increase_indent();
17062
17063 for (auto&& v : arr)
17064 {
17065 if (!parent_is_array)
17066 {
17067 print_newline();
17068 print_indent();
17069 }
17070 parent_is_array = false;
17071
17072 print_unformatted("- "sv);
17073
17074 const auto type = v.type();
17075 TOML_ASSUME(type != node_type::none);
17076 switch (type)
17077 {
17078 case node_type::table: print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&v), true); break;
17079 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&v), true); break;
17080 case node_type::string: print_yaml_string(*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&v)); break;
17081 default: print_value(v, type);
17082 }
17083 }
17084
17085 decrease_indent();
17086 }
17087
17088 TOML_EXTERNAL_LINKAGE
17089 void yaml_formatter::print()
17090 {
17091 if (dump_failed_parse_result())
17092 return;
17093
17094 switch (auto source_type = source().type())
17095 {
17096 case node_type::table:
17097 decrease_indent(); // so root kvps and tables have the same indent
17098 print(*reinterpret_cast<const table*>(&source()));
17099 break;
17100
17101 case node_type::array: print(*reinterpret_cast<const array*>(&source())); break;
17102
17103 case node_type::string: print_yaml_string(*reinterpret_cast<const value<std::string>*>(&source())); break;
17104
17105 default: print_value(source(), source_type);
17106 }
17107 }
17108}
